:ClassIAQuinidineProcainamide :hasReference :R004 .
:ClassIAQuinidineProcainamide :hasSubstanceDescription "Precise role in antiarrhythmic therapy has not been established. Some experts recommend that disopyramide be reserved for use as an alternative drug when lidocaine, quinidine, or procainamide is ineffective or adverse effects of these drugs are intolerable." .

:ClassIIIAmiodaroneSotalol :hasReference :R045 .
:ClassIIIAmiodaroneSotalol :hasReference :R004 .
:ClassIIIAmiodaroneSotalol :hasSubstanceDescription "Used to suppress and prevent recurrence of documented life-threatening ventricular arrhythmias (e.g., sustained ventricular tachycardia); designated an orphan drug by FDA for such use." .

:Clindamycin :hasReference :R081 .
:Clindamycin :hasSubstanceDescription "Clindamycin is an antibiotic that fights bacteria in the body. Clindamycin is used to treat serious infections caused by bacteria." .
