:Colchicine :hasSubstanceDescription "Colchicine is an oral, plant-based prescription alkaloid derived from the dried seeds of the autumn crocus or meadow saffron (Colchicum autumnale) that, depending on the brand or generic, may be used to treat and prevent gout flares in adults." .
:Colchicine :hasReference :R014 .
:Colchicine :hasReference :R068 .
:Colchicine :hasReference :R009 .

:CombinedOralContraceptives :hasReference :R038 .
:CombinedOralContraceptives :hasSubstanceDescription "Combined oral contraceptives (COCs) contain an estrogen and a progestin to prevent ovulation (the release of an egg from an ovary), thin the uterine lining, and thicken cervical mucus making it impenetrable to sperm." .
:CombinedOralContraceptives :hasReference :R011 .

:Contraceptives :hasReference :R038 .
:Contraceptives :hasSubstanceDescription "COCs prevent pregnancy by inhibiting the normal process of ovulation (the release of an egg from an ovary) and by altering the lining of the uterus (the endometrium) so that it is unable to support a fertilized egg. They also change the viscosity (stickiness) of mucus within the cervix to make it hard for sperm to travel to the uterus." .
:Contraceptives :hasReference :R003 .

:Corticosteroids :hasSubstanceDescription "Corticosteroids (adrenal cortical steroids) are natural hormones made by the adrenal cortex which are important in maintaining good health." .
:Corticosteroids :hasReference :R004 .
:Corticosteroids :hasReference :R051 .
:Corticosteroids :hasReference :R010 .

