:I165 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of Pyelonephritis include cloudy or bloody urine which may have a fould or strong odor, low grade fever in some people, pain or burning with urination, pressure or cramping in the lower abdomen or back, and strong need to urinate often even right after the bladd has been emptied. If the infection spread to your kidneys, symptoms may include chills and shaking, fatigue and generally ill feeling, fever above 38.3°C, pain (side, back, or groin), flushed, warmed, or reddened skin, confusion, nausea and vomiting, and sometime severe abdominal pain." .
:I165 :hasReference :R292 .

:I166 :hasReference :R291 .
:I166 :hasReference :R027 .
:I166 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of Cystitis include cloudy or bloody urine, strong or foul-smelling urine, low fever (most people will not have a fever), pain or burning with urination, pressure or cramping in the lower middle abdomen or back, and strong need to urinate often, even right after the bladder has been emptied." .
:I166 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .

:I167 :hasReference :R290 .
:I167 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I167 :hasReference :R027 .
:I167 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of urethritis in men include blood in the urine or semen, burning pain while urinating (dysuria), discharge from the penis, fever (rare), frequent or urgent urination, itching, tenderness or swelling in the penis, enlarged lymph nodes in the groin area, and pain during intercourse or ejaculation. In women, symptoms may include abdominal pain, burning pain while urinating, fever and chills, frequent or urgent urination, pelvic pain, pain during intercourse, and vaginal discharge." .

:I168 :hasReference :R027 .
:I168 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I168 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of sinusitis can include fever, weakness, fatigue, cough, and congestion. There may also be mucus drainage in the back of the throat, called postnasal drip." .
:I168 :hasReference :R294 .

:I169 :hasReference :R027 .
:I169 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of tonsillitis include a sore throat that may be severe, red and swollen tonsils, difficulty swallowing, a white or yellow coating on the tonsils, swollen glands in the neck, fever, and bad breath." .
:I169 :hasReference :R298 .
:I169 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .

:I170 :hasReference :R222 .
:I170 :hasReference :R027 .
:I170 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I170 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of Pharyngitis is sore throat. Other symptoms may include fever, headache, joint pain and muscle aches, skin rashes, and swollen lymph nodes (glands) in the neck." .

:I171 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of acute otitis media vary by age. In infants, the main signs may include irritability or inconsolable crying, fever, and trouble sleeping, while in older children and adults symptoms can include ear pain, fullness in the ear, general feeling of illness, nasal congestion, cough, lethargy, vomiting, diarrhea, hearing loss in the affected ear, drainage of fluid from the ear, and loss of appetite." .
:I171 :hasReference :R027 .
:I171 :hasReference :R299 .
:I171 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .

:I172 :hasReference :R028 .
:I172 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of acute otitis media vary by age. In infants, the main signs may include irritability or inconsolable crying, fever, and trouble sleeping, while in older children and adults symptoms can include ear pain, fullness in the ear, general feeling of illness, nasal congestion, cough, lethargy, vomiting, diarrhea, hearing loss in the affected ear, drainage of fluid from the ear, and loss of appetite." .
:I172 :hasReference :R299 .
:I172 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .

:I173 :hasReference :R222 .
:I173 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of Pharyngitis is sore throat. Other symptoms may include fever, headache, joint pain and muscle aches, skin rashes, and swollen lymph nodes (glands) in the neck." .
:I173 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I173 :hasReference :R028 .

:I174 :hasReference :R028 .
:I174 :hasReference :R318 .
:I174 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I174 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of lower respiratory tract infection (such as RSV infection) include runny nose, decreased appetite, cough, sneezing, fever, and wheezing." .

:I175 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I175 :hasReference :R028 .
:I175 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of acute bronchitis include chest discomfort, a cough that produces mucus (which may be clear or yellow-green), fatigue, low-grade fever, shortness of breath that worsens with activity, and wheezing in people with asthma. After the infection clears, a dry, nagging cough may persist for 1 to 4 weeks." .
:I175 :hasReference :R303 .

:I176 :hasReference :R028 .
:I176 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I176 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of urinary tract infection include pain or burning when urinating, fever, tiredness or shakiness, an urge to urinate often, pressure in the lower abdomen, urine that smells bad or looks cloudy or reddish, and pain in the back or side below the ribs." .
:I176 :hasReference :R300 .

:I177 :hasReference :R029 .
:I177 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of acute bronchitis include chest discomfort, a cough that produces mucus (which may be clear or yellow-green), fatigue, low-grade fever, shortness of breath that worsens with activity, and wheezing in people with asthma. After the infection clears, a dry, nagging cough may persist for 1 to 4 weeks." .
:I177 :hasReference :R303 .
:I177 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .

:I178 :hasReference :R295 .
:I178 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I178 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of chronic bronchitis may be mild or absent at first but typically worsen over time, and can include frequent coughing or a cough that produces a lot of mucus, wheezing, a whistling or squeaky sound when breathing, shortness of breath especially during physical activity, and a feeling of tightness in the chest; some individuals may also experience frequent respiratory infections such as colds and the flu, and in severe cases, weight loss, weakness in the lower muscles, and swelling in the ankles, feet, or legs." .
:I178 :hasReference :R029 .

:I179 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I179 :hasReference :R288 .
:I179 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of Bronchiectasis include a long-term (chronic) cough with large amounts of foul-smelling sputum, along with breath odor, coughing up blood (less common in children), fatigue, paleness, shortness of breath that worsens with exercise, weight loss, wheezing, low-grade fever, night sweats, and, in rare cases, clubbing of the fingers depending on the underlying cause." .
:I179 :hasReference :R029 .

:I180 :hasReference :R029 .
:I180 :hasReference :R318 .
:I180 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I180 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of upper respiratory tract infection include sneezing, a stuffy or congested nose, runny nose, sore throat, coughing, and headache." .

:I181 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
:I181 :hasReference :R029 .
:I181 :hasReference :R219 .
:I181 :hasSymptoms "Symptoms of Pneumonia can range from mild to severe and include fever, chills, cough (usually with phlegm), shortness of breath, chest pain when you breathe or cough, nausea and/or vomiting, and diarrhea." .

:I182 :hasSeverityType :NotSpecified .
