:Ritonavir :hasReference :R090 .
:Ritonavir :hasReference :R016 .
:Ritonavir :hasReference :R014 .
:Ritonavir :hasSubstanceDescription "Ritonavir is an antiviral medicine that prevents human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) from multiplying in your body. Ritonavir is used together with other antiviral medicines to treat HIV, the virus that can cause acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS). Ritonavir is not a cure for HIV or AIDS." .

:Rosiglitazone :hasReference :R020 .
:Rosiglitazone :hasSubstanceDescription "Rosiglitazone is used to treat a type of diabetes mellitus called type 2 diabetes. It may be used alone or with other medicines such as metformin or sulfonylurea agents. Rosiglitazone is used together with a proper diet and exercise to help control blood sugar levels. It does this by helping your body use insulin better." .
:Rosiglitazone :hasReference :R116 .

:SE001 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE001 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE001 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE001 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .

:SE002 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE002 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE002 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE002 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .

:SE003 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE003 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE003 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE003 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE004 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE004 :hasPattern :Infrequent .
:SE004 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE004 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE005 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE005 :hasReference :R135 .
:SE005 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE005 :hasReference :R001 .

:SE006 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE006 :hasReference :R136 .
:SE006 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE006 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysphagia is a term that means difficulty swallowing. Usually, when you swallow, food moves easily from your mouth, down your throat, and into your stomach." .

:SE007 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE007 :hasPattern :Rare .
:SE007 :hasSideEffectDescription "Esophagitis is a condition in which the lining of the esophagus becomes swollen, inflamed, or irritated. The esophagus is the tube that leads from your mouth to the stomach." .
:SE007 :hasReference :R137 .

:SE008 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE008 :hasSideEffectDescription "Maculopapular rash is a flat red rash." .
:SE008 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE008 :hasReference :R138 .

:SE009 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE009 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE009 :hasReference :R139 .
:SE009 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythroderma is one alternative name of Exfoliative dermatitis. It is widespread readness of the skin. It also accompanied by scaling, peeling, and flaking of the skin, and may include utching and hair loss." .

:SE010 :hasSideEffectDescription "A BUN, or blood urea nitrogen test, measures the amount of urea nitrogen in your blood. Urea nitrogen is a waste product that forms as your body breaks down proteins. It's carried in your blood and then removed by your kidneys when you urinate (pee)." .
:SE010 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE010 :hasReference :R140 .
:SE010 :hasReference :R001 .

:SE011 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE011 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE011 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE011 :hasReference :R141 .

:SE012 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE012 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioneurotic Edema's alternative name is Angioedema. It is swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE012 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE012 :hasReference :R142 .

:SE013 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE013 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE013 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a serious allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE013 :hasReference :R001 .

:SE014 :hasReference :R144 .
:SE014 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE014 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .
:SE014 :hasReference :R001 .

:SE015 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE015 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE015 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pericarditis is a condition in which the sac-like covering around the heart (pericardium) becomes inflamed." .
:SE015 :hasReference :R145 .

:SE016 :hasSideEffectDescription "Systemic Lupus Erythematosus is a chronic disease that causes inflammation in connective tissues, such as cartilage and the lining of blood vessels, which provide strength and flexibility to structures throughout the body." .
:SE016 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE016 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE016 :hasReference :R146 .

:SE017 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE017 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE017 :hasReference :R147 .
:SE017 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE018 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE018 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE018 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE018 :hasReference :R149 .

:SE019 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE019 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE019 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE019 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .

:SE020 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE020 :hasReference :R001 .
:SE020 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE020 :hasReference :R151 .

:SE021 :hasPattern :Infrequent .
:SE021 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE021 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE021 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE022 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE022 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE022 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE022 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .

:SE023 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE023 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE023 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE023 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE024 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE024 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE024 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE024 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE025 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE025 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE025 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE025 :hasReference :R135 .

:SE026 :hasReference :R136 .
:SE026 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE026 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysphagia is a term that means difficulty swallowing. Usually, when you swallow, food moves easily from your mouth, down your throat, and into your stomach." .
:SE026 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE027 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .
:SE027 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE027 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE027 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE028 :hasSideEffectDescription "Reversible upon drug discontinuation and professional dental cleaning has been reported." .
:SE028 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE028 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE029 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE029 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE029 :hasSideEffectDescription "May occur with drugs of the tetracycline class when used during tooth development." .

:SE030 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE030 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE030 :hasSideEffectDescription "May occur with drugs of the tetracycline class when used during tooth development." .

:SE031 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE031 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Toxic Epidermal Necrolysis represents the more severe end." .
:SE031 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE031 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE032 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE032 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE032 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE032 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .

:SE033 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE033 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .
:SE033 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE033 :hasReference :R154 .

:SE034 :hasSideEffectDescription "Skin pigmentation disorders affect the color of your skin. Your skin gets its color from a pigment called melanin. Special cells in the skin make melanin. When these cells become damaged or unhealthy, it affects melanin production. Some pigmentation disorders affect just patches of skin. Others affect your entire body." .
:SE034 :hasReference :R155 .
:SE034 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE034 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE035 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE035 :hasSideEffectDescription "Maculopapular rash is a flat red rash." .
:SE035 :hasReference :R138 .
:SE035 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE036 :hasReference :R139 .
:SE036 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE036 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythroderma is one alternative name of Exfoliative dermatitis. It is widespread readness of the skin. It also accompanied by scaling, peeling, and flaking of the skin, and may include utching and hair loss." .
:SE036 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE037 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE037 :hasReference :R156 .
:SE037 :hasSideEffectDescription "Photosensitivity is an increased sensitivity to sunlight." .
:SE037 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE038 :hasReference :R140 .
:SE038 :hasSideEffectDescription "A BUN, or blood urea nitrogen test, measures the amount of urea nitrogen in your blood. Urea nitrogen is a waste product that forms as your body breaks down proteins. It's carried in your blood and then removed by your kidneys when you urinate (pee)." .
:SE038 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE038 :hasPattern :DoseRelated .

:SE039 :hasReference :R141 .
:SE039 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE039 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE039 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE040 :hasReference :R142 .
:SE040 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE040 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioneurotic Edema's alternative name is Angioedema. It is swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE040 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE041 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE041 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE041 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE041 :hasReference :R143 .

:SE042 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .
:SE042 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE042 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE042 :hasReference :R144 .

:SE043 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE043 :hasReference :R145 .
:SE043 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE043 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pericarditis is a condition in which the sac-like covering around the heart (pericardium) becomes inflamed." .

:SE044 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE044 :hasReference :R146 .
:SE044 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE044 :hasSideEffectDescription "Systemic Lupus Erythematosus is a chronic disease that causes inflammation in connective tissues, such as cartilage and the lining of blood vessels, which provide strength and flexibility to structures throughout the body." .

:SE045 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE045 :hasSideEffectDescription "Jarisch-Herxheimer reaction has been reported in the setting of spirochete infections treated with doxycycline." .
:SE045 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE046 :hasReference :R147 .
:SE046 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE046 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE046 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE047 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE047 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE047 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE047 :hasReference :R149 .

:SE048 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE048 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .
:SE048 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE048 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE049 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE049 :hasReference :R151 .
:SE049 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE049 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE050 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE050 :hasSideEffectDescription "Intracranial Hypertension is a rise in the pressure inside the skull that can result from or cause brain injury." .
:SE050 :hasReference :R157 .
:SE050 :hasReference :R002 .

:SE051 :hasReference :R002 .
:SE051 :hasSideEffectDescription "Brown-black microscopic discoloration of the thyroid gland." .
:SE051 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE052 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE052 :hasReference :R003 .
:SE052 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE052 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .

:SE053 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE053 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE053 :hasReference :R003 .
:SE053 :hasReference :R133 .

:SE054 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE054 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE054 :hasReference :R003 .
:SE054 :hasReference :R133 .

:SE055 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE055 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE055 :hasReference :R003 .
:SE055 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE056 :hasReference :R003 .
:SE056 :hasReference :R135 .
:SE056 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE056 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE057 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysphagia is a term that means difficulty swallowing. Usually, when you swallow, food moves easily from your mouth, down your throat, and into your stomach." .
:SE057 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE057 :hasReference :R136 .
:SE057 :hasReference :R003 .

:SE058 :hasReference :R003 .
:SE058 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE058 :hasSideEffectDescription "Maculopapular rash is a flat red rash." .
:SE058 :hasReference :R138 .

