:SE069 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE069 :hasReference :R158 .
:SE069 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE069 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .

:SE070 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE070 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE070 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE070 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .

:SE071 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE071 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE071 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE071 :hasPattern :Common .

:SE072 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE072 :hasReference :R161 .
:SE072 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE072 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspnea is shortness of breath." .

:SE073 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE073 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE073 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE073 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .

:SE074 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE074 :hasReference :R134 .
:SE074 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE074 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .

:SE075 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE075 :hasSideEffectDescription "Constipation means having fewer than three bowel movements a week. The stool (poop) can be hard and dry. Sometimes it is painful to pass. At one time or another, almost everyone gets constipated. In most cases, it lasts a short time and is not serious." .
:SE075 :hasReference :R162 .
:SE075 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE076 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE076 :hasReference :R163 .
:SE076 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE076 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE077 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE077 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE077 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE077 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE078 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE078 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .
:SE078 :hasReference :R164 .
:SE078 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE079 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE079 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE079 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE079 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE080 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pruritus is an alternative name for Itching. It is a tingling or irritation of the skin that makes you want to scratch the area. Itching may occur all over the body or only in one location." .
:SE080 :hasReference :R166 .
:SE080 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE080 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE081 :hasReference :R167 .
:SE081 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginitis, also called vulvovaginitis, is an inflammation or infection of the vagina. It can also affect the vulva, which is the external part of a woman's genitals. Vaginitis can cause itching, pain, discharge, and odor." .
:SE081 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE081 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE082 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE082 :hasReference :R168 .
:SE082 :hasSideEffectDescription "Edema means swelling caused by fluid in your body's tissues. It usually occurs in the feet, ankles and legs, but it can involve your entire body." .
:SE082 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE083 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE083 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .
:SE083 :hasReference :R189 .
:SE083 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE084 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE084 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE084 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anemia is also called iron poor blood. Anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE084 :hasReference :R190 .

:SE085 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE085 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE085 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE085 :hasReference :R149 .

:SE086 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hyperglycemia means high blood glucose. It most often affects people who have diabetes. When you have diabetes, your body doesn't make enough insulin or can't use it the right way. Too much glucose stays in your blood and doesn't reach your cells." .
:SE086 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE086 :hasReference :R169 .
:SE086 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE087 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE087 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE087 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypoglycemia means low glucose. It happens when the level of glucose in your blood drops below what is healthy for you." .
:SE087 :hasReference :R170 .

:SE088 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE088 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anxiety is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness. It might cause you to sweat, feel restless and tense, and have a rapid heartbeat. It can be a normal reaction to stress." .
:SE088 :hasReference :R171 .
:SE088 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE089 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE089 :hasReference :R172 .
:SE089 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agitation is an unpleasant state of extreme arousal. An agitated person may feel stirred up, excited, tense, confused, or irritable." .
:SE089 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE090 :hasReference :R173 .
:SE090 :hasSideEffectDescription "Confusion is the inability to think as clearly or quickly as you normally do. You may feel disoriented and have difficulty paying attention, remembering, and making decisions." .
:SE090 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE090 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE091 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE091 :hasSideEffectDescription "A tremor is a neurological condition that includes shaking or trembling movements in one or more parts of your body. It most often affects the hands. But it can also affect the arms, legs, head, vocal cords, and torso (trunk). A tremor is involuntary, meaning that you cannot control it. It happens because of muscle contractions." .
:SE091 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE091 :hasReference :R174 .

:SE092 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE092 :hasSideEffectDescription "Paresthesia is an alternative name of Numbness and Tingling. These are abnormal sensations that can occur anywhere in your body, but they are often felt in your fingers, hands, feet, arms, or legs." .
:SE092 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE092 :hasReference :R175 .

:SE093 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE093 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE093 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE093 :hasReference :R160 .

:SE094 :hasReference :R176 .
:SE094 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE094 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE094 :hasSideEffectDescription "Walking abnormalities can be caused by many different types of problems. Problems with the joints, (such as arthritis), bones (such as deformities), circulation (such as peripheral vascular disease), or even pain can make it difficult to walk properly. Diseases or injuries to the nerves, muscles, brain, spinal cord, or inner ear can affect normal walking." .

:SE095 :hasSideEffectDescription "Somnolence is an alternative name of drowsiness. It refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day." .
:SE095 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE095 :hasReference :R177 .
:SE095 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE096 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE096 :hasReference :R178 .
:SE096 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE096 :hasSideEffectDescription "Syncope is also called Fainting. It is a temporary loss of consciousness. If you're about to faint, you'll feel dizzy, lightheaded, or nauseous. Your field of vision may \"white out\" or \"black out.\" Your skin may be cold and clammy. You lose muscle control at the same time, and may fall down." .

:SE097 :hasReference :R179 .
:SE097 :hasSideEffectDescription "Epistaxis is an alternative name of nose bleed. It is a loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose. Bleeding most often occurs from one nostril only." .
:SE097 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE097 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE098 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE098 :hasReference :R180 .
:SE098 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE098 :hasSideEffectDescription "Cardiac arrest occurs when the heart suddenly stops beating. When this happens, blood flow to the brain and the rest of the body also stops. Cardiac arrest is a medical emergency. If it is not treated within a few minutes, cardiac arrest most often causes death." .

:SE099 :hasReference :R181 .
:SE099 :hasSideEffectDescription "Palpitations are feelings or sensations that your heart is pounding or racing. They can be felt in your chest, throat, or neck." .
:SE099 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE099 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE100 :hasSideEffectDescription "Ventricular tachycardia (VT) is a rapid heartbeat that starts in the lower chambers of the heart (ventricles)." .
:SE100 :hasReference :R182 .
:SE100 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE100 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE101 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE101 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE101 :hasSideEffectDescription "Venticular Fibrillation (VF) is a severely abnormal heart rhythm (arrythmia) that is life threatening." .
:SE101 :hasReference :R186 .

:SE102 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastritis occurs when the lining of the stomach becomes inflamed or swollen. Gastritis may last for only a short time (acute gastritis) or it may linger for month to years (chronic gastritis)." .
:SE102 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE102 :hasReference :R187 .
:SE102 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE103 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE103 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE103 :hasReference :R188 .
:SE103 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stomatitis is a viral infection of the mouth that causes sores and ulcers. These mouth ulcers are not the same as canker sores, which are not caused by a virus." .

:SE104 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE104 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE104 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE104 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .

:SE105 :hasSideEffectDescription "Esophagitis is a condition in which the lining of the esophagus becomes swollen, inflamed, or irritated. The esophagus is the tube that leads from your mouth to the stomach." .
:SE105 :hasReference :R137 .
:SE105 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE105 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE106 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE106 :hasReference :R201 .
:SE106 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE106 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastroenteritis is an inflammation of the lining of the stomach and intestines. The main symptoms include vomiting and diarrhea. It is usually not serious in healthy people, but it can sometimes lead to dehydration or cause severe symptoms." .

:SE107 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE107 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE107 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE107 :hasReference :R135 .

:SE108 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatic lipase deficiency is a disorder that affects the body's ability to break down fats (lipids). People with this disorder have increased amounts of certain fats, known as triglycerides and cholesterol, in the blood." .
:SE108 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE108 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE108 :hasReference :R185 .

:SE109 :hasReference :R141 .
:SE109 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE109 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE109 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE110 :hasReference :R191 .
:SE110 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE110 :hasSideEffectDescription "Arthralgia is an alternative name of joint pain. It can affect one or more joints. Joint pain can be caused by many types of injuries or conditions. It may be linked to arthritis, bursitis, and muscle pain." .
:SE110 :hasReference :R004 .

:SE111 :hasReference :R004 .
:SE111 :hasReference :R192 .
:SE111 :hasSideEffectDescription "Acute Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .
:SE111 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE112 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE112 :hasSideEffectDescription "Moniliasis is also called yeast infections. It is a fungus that lives almost everywhere, including in your body. Usually, your immune system keeps yeast under control." .
:SE112 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE112 :hasReference :R193 .

:SE113 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .
:SE113 :hasReference :R158 .
:SE113 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE113 :hasPattern :Common .

