:SE124 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE124 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pruritus is an alternative name for Itching. It is a tingling or irritation of the skin that makes you want to scratch the area. Itching may occur all over the body or only in one location." .
:SE124 :hasReference :R166 .

:SE125 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginitis, also called vulvovaginitis, is an inflammation or infection of the vagina. It can also affect the vulva, which is the external part of a woman's genitals. Vaginitis can cause itching, pain, discharge, and odor." .
:SE125 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE125 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE125 :hasReference :R167 .

:SE126 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE126 :hasReference :R168 .
:SE126 :hasSideEffectDescription "Edema means swelling caused by fluid in your body's tissues. It usually occurs in the feet, ankles and legs, but it can involve your entire body." .
:SE126 :hasPattern :Common .

:SE127 :hasReference :R189 .
:SE127 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .
:SE127 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE127 :hasPattern :Common .

:SE128 :hasSideEffectDescription "Moniliasis is also called yeast infections. It is a fungus that lives almost everywhere, including in your body. Usually, your immune system keeps yeast under control." .
:SE128 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE128 :hasReference :R193 .
:SE128 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE129 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE129 :hasReference :R190 .
:SE129 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anemia is also called iron poor blood. Anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE129 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE130 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE130 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE130 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE130 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE131 :hasReference :R169 .
:SE131 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE131 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hyperglycemia means high blood glucose. It most often affects people who have diabetes. When you have diabetes, your body doesn't make enough insulin or can't use it the right way. Too much glucose stays in your blood and doesn't reach your cells." .
:SE131 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE132 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE132 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE132 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypoglycemia means low glucose. It happens when the level of glucose in your blood drops below what is healthy for you." .
:SE132 :hasReference :R170 .

:SE133 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE133 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE133 :hasReference :R194 .
:SE133 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hyperkalemia is an alternative name of high potassium level. It is a problem in which the amount of potassium in the blood is higher than normal." .

:SE134 :hasReference :R171 .
:SE134 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anxiety is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness. It might cause you to sweat, feel restless and tense, and have a rapid heartbeat. It can be a normal reaction to stress." .
:SE134 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE134 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE135 :hasReference :R172 .
:SE135 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agitation is an unpleasant state of extreme arousal. An agitated person may feel stirred up, excited, tense, confused, or irritable." .
:SE135 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE135 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE136 :hasSideEffectDescription "Confusion is the inability to think as clearly or quickly as you normally do. You may feel disoriented and have difficulty paying attention, remembering, and making decisions." .
:SE136 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE136 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE136 :hasReference :R173 .

:SE137 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE137 :hasReference :R195 .
:SE137 :hasSideEffectDescription "Depression is more than a feeling of being sad or irritable for a few days. It's a serious mood disorder." .
:SE137 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE138 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE138 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE138 :hasReference :R196 .
:SE138 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hallucinations involve sensing things such as visions, sounds, or smells that seem real but are not. These things are created by the mind." .

:SE139 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE139 :hasReference :R197 .
:SE139 :hasSideEffectDescription "A nightmare is a bad dream that brings out strong feelings of fear, terror, distress, or anxiety." .
:SE139 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE140 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE140 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE140 :hasSideEffectDescription "Sleep disorders are conditions that disturb your normal sleep patterns." .
:SE140 :hasReference :R198 .

:SE141 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE141 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE141 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .
:SE141 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE142 :hasReference :R174 .
:SE142 :hasSideEffectDescription "A tremor is a neurological condition that includes shaking or trembling movements in one or more parts of your body. It most often affects the hands. But it can also affect the arms, legs, head, vocal cords, and torso (trunk). A tremor is involuntary, meaning that you cannot control it. It happens because of muscle contractions." .
:SE142 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE142 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE143 :hasReference :R199 .
:SE143 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE143 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE143 :hasSideEffectDescription "Convulsions can also be called as Seizures. These are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .

:SE144 :hasReference :R175 .
:SE144 :hasSideEffectDescription "Paresthesia is an alternative name of Numbness and Tingling. These are abnormal sensations that can occur anywhere in your body, but they are often felt in your fingers, hands, feet, arms, or legs." .
:SE144 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE144 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE145 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE145 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE145 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE145 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE146 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypertonia is increased muscle tone." .
:SE146 :hasReference :R200 .
:SE146 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE146 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE147 :hasSideEffectDescription "Walking abnormalities can be caused by many different types of problems. Problems with the joints, (such as arthritis), bones (such as deformities), circulation (such as peripheral vascular disease), or even pain can make it difficult to walk properly. Diseases or injuries to the nerves, muscles, brain, spinal cord, or inner ear can affect normal walking." .
:SE147 :hasReference :R176 .
:SE147 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE147 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE148 :hasSideEffectDescription "Somnolence is an alternative name of drowsiness. It refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day." .
:SE148 :hasReference :R177 .
:SE148 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE148 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE149 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE149 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE149 :hasReference :R178 .
:SE149 :hasSideEffectDescription "Syncope is also called Fainting. It is a temporary loss of consciousness. If you're about to faint, you'll feel dizzy, lightheaded, or nauseous. Your field of vision may \"white out\" or \"black out.\" Your skin may be cold and clammy. You lose muscle control at the same time, and may fall down." .

:SE150 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE150 :hasSideEffectDescription "Epistaxis is an alternative name of nose bleed. It is a loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose. Bleeding most often occurs from one nostril only." .
:SE150 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE150 :hasReference :R179 .

:SE151 :hasReference :R180 .
:SE151 :hasSideEffectDescription "Cardiac arrest occurs when the heart suddenly stops beating. When this happens, blood flow to the brain and the rest of the body also stops. Cardiac arrest is a medical emergency. If it is not treated within a few minutes, cardiac arrest most often causes death." .
:SE151 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE151 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE152 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE152 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE152 :hasSideEffectDescription "Palpitations are feelings or sensations that your heart is pounding or racing. They can be felt in your chest, throat, or neck." .
:SE152 :hasReference :R181 .

:SE153 :hasSideEffectDescription "Ventricular tachycardia (VT) is a rapid heartbeat that starts in the lower chambers of the heart (ventricles)." .
:SE153 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE153 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE153 :hasReference :R182 .

:SE154 :hasSideEffectDescription "Venticular Fibrillation (VF) is a severely abnormal heart rhythm (arrythmia) that is life threatening." .
:SE154 :hasReference :R186 .
:SE154 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE154 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE155 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE155 :hasSideEffectDescription "Phlebitis is an alternative name of Thrombophlebitis. It is a swelling (inflammation) of a vein. A blood clot (thrombus) in the vein is the most common cause of this swelling." .
:SE155 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE155 :hasReference :R202 .

:SE156 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastritis occurs when the lining of the stomach becomes inflamed or swollen. Gastritis may last for only a short time (acute gastritis) or it may linger for month to years (chronic gastritis)." .
:SE156 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE156 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE156 :hasReference :R187 .

:SE157 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE157 :hasReference :R188 .
:SE157 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE157 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stomatitis is a viral infection of the mouth that causes sores and ulcers. These mouth ulcers are not the same as canker sores, which are not caused by a virus." .

:SE158 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .
:SE158 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE158 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE158 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE159 :hasSideEffectDescription "Esophagitis is a condition in which the lining of the esophagus becomes swollen, inflamed, or irritated. The esophagus is the tube that leads from your mouth to the stomach." .
:SE159 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE159 :hasReference :R137 .
:SE159 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE160 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE160 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastroenteritis is an inflammation of the lining of the stomach and intestines. The main symptoms include vomiting and diarrhea. It is usually not serious in healthy people, but it can sometimes lead to dehydration or cause severe symptoms." .
:SE160 :hasReference :R201 .
:SE160 :hasReference :R005 .

:SE161 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE161 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE161 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE161 :hasReference :R135 .

:SE162 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .
:SE162 :hasReference :R203 .
:SE162 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE162 :hasPattern :LessCommon .

:SE163 :hasReference :R185 .
:SE163 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE163 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE163 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatic lipase deficiency is a disorder that affects the body's ability to break down fats (lipids). People with this disorder have increased amounts of certain fats, known as triglycerides and cholesterol, in the blood." .

:SE164 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE164 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE164 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE164 :hasReference :R141 .

:SE165 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE165 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE165 :hasSideEffectDescription "Arthralgia is an alternative name of joint pain. It can affect one or more joints. Joint pain can be caused by many types of injuries or conditions. It may be linked to arthritis, bursitis, and muscle pain." .
:SE165 :hasReference :R191 .

:SE166 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE166 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE166 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tendonitis is also called Tendinitis. It usually happens after repeated injury to an area such as the wrist or ankle. It causes pain and soreness around a joint. Some common forms of tendinitis are named after the sports that increase their risk." .
:SE166 :hasReference :R204 .

:SE167 :hasPattern :LessCommon .
:SE167 :hasReference :R005 .
:SE167 :hasSideEffectDescription "Acute Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .
:SE167 :hasReference :R192 .

:SE168 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Toxic Epidermal Necrolysis represents the more severe end." .
:SE168 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE168 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE168 :hasReference :R006 .

:SE169 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE169 :hasReference :R205 .
:SE169 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE169 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancytopenia can result in extreme tiredness (fatigue) due to low numbers of red blood cells (anemia), frequent infections due to low numbers of white blood cells (neutropenia), and abnormal bleeding due to low numbers of platelets (thrombocytopenia)" .

:SE170 :hasReference :R148 .
:SE170 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE170 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE170 :hasSideEffectDescription "Autoimmune hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide the oxygen to the body's tissue." .

:SE171 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE171 :hasReference :R206 .
:SE171 :hasSideEffectDescription "QT interval prolongation is an irregular heart Prolongation of the QT Interval." .
:SE171 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE172 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE172 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE172 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylactic Shock is an alternative name for Anaphylaxis. It is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE172 :hasReference :R006 .

:SE173 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE173 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylactoid Reaction is an anaphylactic-like reaction." .
:SE173 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE173 :hasReference :R006 .

:SE174 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysphonia is an alternative name for Hoarseness. It refers to difficulty making sounds when trying to speak. Vocal sounds may be weak, breathy, scratchy, or husky, and the pitch or quality of the voice may change." .
:SE174 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE174 :hasReference :R207 .
:SE174 :hasReference :R006 .

:SE175 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE175 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE175 :hasSideEffectDescription "An electroencephalogram (EEG) is a test to measure the electrical activity of the brain. Abnormal results on an EEG test may be due to abnormal bleeding in the braon, an abnormal structure in the brain, and others." .
:SE175 :hasReference :R208 .

:SE176 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE176 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE176 :hasSideEffectDescription "Encephalopathy is an abnormal brain function." .
:SE176 :hasReference :R209 .

:SE177 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE177 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE177 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE177 :hasReference :R151 .

:SE178 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE178 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .
:SE178 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE178 :hasReference :R154 .

:SE179 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE179 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE179 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE179 :hasReference :R147 .

:SE180 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE180 :hasReference :R210 .
:SE180 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE180 :hasSideEffectDescription "Peripheral neuropathy means these nerves don't work properly. Peripheral neuropathy may occur because of damage to a single nerve or a group of nerves. It may also affect nerves in the whole body." .

:SE181 :hasReference :R211 .
:SE181 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE181 :hasSideEffectDescription "Rhabdomyolysis is the breakdown of muscle tissue that leads to the release of muscle fiber contents into the blood. These substances are harmful to the kidney and often cause kidney damage." .
:SE181 :hasReference :R006 .

:SE182 :hasReference :R006 .
:SE182 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .
:SE182 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE182 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE183 :hasReference :R007 .
:SE183 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE183 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE183 :hasSideEffectDescription "A skin rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .

:SE184 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE184 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE184 :hasReference :R007 .
:SE184 :hasReference :R141 .

:SE185 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE185 :hasReference :R007 .
:SE185 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE185 :hasReference :R151 .

:SE186 :hasReference :R212 .
:SE186 :hasReference :R007 .
:SE186 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE186 :hasSideEffectDescription "A fever is a body temperature that is higher than normal. A normal temperature can vary from person to person, but it is usually around 98.6 °F (37 °C). A fever is not a disease. It is usually a sign that your body is trying to fight an illness or infection." .

:SE187 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .
:SE187 :hasReference :R144 .
:SE187 :hasReference :R007 .
:SE187 :hasPattern :Common .

:SE188 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE188 :hasReference :R007 .
:SE188 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE188 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .

:SE189 :hasSideEffectDescription "An arrhythmia is a problem with the rate or rhythm of your heartbeat. Your heart beats too quickly, too slowly, or with an irregular pattern. Changes in the electrical signals that control your heartbeat cause arrhythmias." .
:SE189 :hasReference :R216 .
:SE189 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE189 :hasReference :R007 .

:SE190 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE190 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE190 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE190 :hasReference :R008 .

:SE191 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE191 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE191 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE191 :hasReference :R133 .

:SE192 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE192 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE192 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE192 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE193 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE193 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE193 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE193 :hasReference :R163 .

:SE194 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE194 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE194 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE194 :hasPattern :Rare .

:SE195 :hasSideEffectDescription "Palpitations are feelings or sensations that your heart is pounding or racing. They can be felt in your chest, throat, or neck." .
:SE195 :hasReference :R181 .
:SE195 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE195 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE196 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE196 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .
:SE196 :hasReference :R189 .
:SE196 :hasReference :R008 .

:SE197 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE197 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE197 :hasReference :R164 .
:SE197 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .

:SE198 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE198 :hasReference :R213 .
:SE198 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE198 :hasSideEffectDescription "Flatulence is also called gas. Gas is air in the intestine that is passed through the rectum. Air that moves from the digestive tract through the mouth is called belching." .

:SE199 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE199 :hasReference :R214 .
:SE199 :hasSideEffectDescription "Black or tarry stools with a foul smell are a sign of a problem in the upper digestive tract. It most often indicates that there is bleeding in the esophagus, stomach, or first part of the small intestine. The term melena is used to describe this finding." .
:SE199 :hasReference :R008 .

:SE200 :hasSideEffectDescription "Moniliasis is also called yeast infections. It is a fungus that lives almost everywhere, including in your body. Usually, your immune system keeps yeast under control." .
:SE200 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE200 :hasReference :R193 .
:SE200 :hasReference :R008 .

:SE201 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginitis, also called vulvovaginitis, is an inflammation or infection of the vagina. It can also affect the vulva, which is the external part of a woman's genitals. Vaginitis can cause itching, pain, discharge, and odor." .
:SE201 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE201 :hasReference :R167 .
:SE201 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE202 :hasReference :R217 .
:SE202 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE202 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE202 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nephritis is a kidney disorder in which the spaces between the kidney tubules become swollen (inflamed). This can cause problems with the way your kidneys work." .

:SE203 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE203 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE203 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE203 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE204 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE204 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE204 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE204 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE205 :hasReference :R218 .
:SE205 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE205 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE205 :hasSideEffectDescription "Fatigue is a feeling of weariness, tiredness, or lack of energy. It can interfere with your usual daily activities. Fatigue can be a normal response to physical activity, emotional stress, boredom, or lack of sleep." .

:SE206 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE206 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE206 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE206 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE207 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pruritus is an alternative name for Itching. It is a tingling or irritation of the skin that makes you want to scratch the area. Itching may occur all over the body or only in one location." .
:SE207 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE207 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE207 :hasReference :R166 .

:SE208 :hasSideEffectDescription "Photosensitivity is an increased sensitivity to sunlight." .
:SE208 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE208 :hasReference :R156 .
:SE208 :hasReference :R008 .

:SE209 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioedema is a swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE209 :hasReference :R142 .
:SE209 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE209 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE210 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .
:SE210 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE210 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE210 :hasReference :R150 .

:SE211 :hasReference :R008 .
:SE211 :hasSideEffectDescription "Somnolence is an alternative name of drowsiness. It refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day." .
:SE211 :hasReference :R177 .
:SE211 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE212 :hasReference :R193 .
:SE212 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE212 :hasSideEffectDescription "Candidiasis is also called Yeast Infections.  It is a fungus that lives almost everywhere, including in your body. Usually, your immune system keeps yeast under control." .
:SE212 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE213 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginal Infection is an infection of the vagina. It is most often due to the fungus. Most women have a vaginal yeast infection at some time." .
:SE213 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE213 :hasReference :R215 .
:SE213 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE214 :hasReference :R219 .
:SE214 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pneumonia is an infection in one or both of your lungs. It causes the air sacs of your lungs to fill up with fluid or pus. Pneumonia can range from mild to severe, depending on what caused it, your age, and your overall health." .
:SE214 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE214 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE215 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE215 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE215 :hasSideEffectDescription "If you have ever had athlete's foot or a yeast infection, you can blame a fungus. A fungus is a primitive organism. Mushrooms, mold and mildew are examples. Fungi live in air, in soil, on plants and in water. Some live in the human body. Only about half of all types of fungi are harmful." .
:SE215 :hasReference :R220 .

:SE216 :hasReference :R221 .
:SE216 :hasSideEffectDescription "Bacterial Infection can  give off toxins (poisons) that can damage your cells and make you sick. These bacteria can reproduce quickly in your body." .
:SE216 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE216 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE217 :hasReference :R222 .
:SE217 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE217 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pharyngitis, or sore throat, is discomfort, pain, or scratchiness in the throat. It often makes it painful to swallow." .
:SE217 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE218 :hasReference :R201 .
:SE218 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE218 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE218 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastroenteritis is an inflammation of the lining of the stomach and intestines. The main symptoms include vomiting and diarrhea. It is usually not serious in healthy people, but it can sometimes lead to dehydration or cause severe symptoms." .

:SE219 :hasSideEffectDescription "Rhinitis is a condition that includes a runny nose, sneezing, and nasal stuffiness. When environmental allergies (such as hay fever) or a cold are not causing these symptoms, the condition is called nonallergic rhinitis." .
:SE219 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE219 :hasReference :R223 .
:SE219 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE220 :hasSideEffectDescription "Oral Candidiasis, commonly known as thrush, is a yeast infection of the mouth or throat." .
:SE220 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE220 :hasReference :R184 .
:SE220 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE221 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE221 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE221 :hasReference :R203 .
:SE221 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .

:SE222 :hasSideEffectDescription "Leukopenia is a low white blood count." .
:SE222 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE222 :hasReference :R224 .
:SE222 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE223 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE223 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE223 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .
:SE223 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE224 :hasReference :R151 .
:SE224 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE224 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE224 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .

:SE225 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE225 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE225 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE225 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .

:SE226 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE226 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE226 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioedema is a swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE226 :hasReference :R142 .

:SE227 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE227 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypersensitivity is also called Allergy. It is a reaction by your immune system to something that does not bother most other people. People who have allergies often are sensitive to more than one thing" .
:SE227 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE227 :hasReference :R225 .

:SE228 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE228 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE228 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylactic Shock is an alternative name for Anaphylaxis. It is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE228 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE229 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .
:SE229 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE229 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE229 :hasReference :R132 .

:SE230 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .
:SE230 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE230 :hasReference :R158 .
:SE230 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE231 :hasPattern :Rare .
:SE231 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE231 :hasReference :R172 .
:SE231 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agitation is an unpleasant state of extreme arousal. An agitated person may feel stirred up, excited, tense, confused, or irritable." .

:SE232 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE232 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anxiety is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness. It might cause you to sweat, feel restless and tense, and have a rapid heartbeat. It can be a normal reaction to stress." .
:SE232 :hasReference :R171 .
:SE232 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE233 :hasSideEffectDescription "Delirium is a mental state in which you are confused, disoriented, and not able to think or remember clearly. It usually starts suddenly. It is often temporary and treatable." .
:SE233 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE233 :hasReference :R2264 .
:SE233 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE234 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE234 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE234 :hasReference :R196 .
:SE234 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hallucinations involve sensing things such as visions, sounds, or smells that seem real but are not. These things are created by the mind." .

:SE235 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE235 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE235 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE235 :hasPattern :Common .

:SE236 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE236 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE236 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE236 :hasReference :R160 .

:SE237 :hasReference :R177 .
:SE237 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE237 :hasSideEffectDescription "Somnolence is an alternative name of drowsiness. It refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day." .
:SE237 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE238 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE238 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE238 :hasReference :R175 .
:SE238 :hasSideEffectDescription "Paresthesia is an alternative name of Numbness and Tingling. These are abnormal sensations that can occur anywhere in your body, but they are often felt in your fingers, hands, feet, arms, or legs." .

:SE239 :hasReference :R178 .
:SE239 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE239 :hasSideEffectDescription "Syncope is also called Fainting. It is a temporary loss of consciousness. If you're about to faint, you'll feel dizzy, lightheaded, or nauseous. Your field of vision may \"white out\" or \"black out.\" Your skin may be cold and clammy. You lose muscle control at the same time, and may fall down." .
:SE239 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE240 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE240 :hasSideEffectDescription "Convulsions can also be called as Seizures. These are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .
:SE240 :hasReference :R199 .
:SE240 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE241 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE241 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE241 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anosmia is when the sense of smell is completely absent." .
:SE241 :hasReference :R227 .

:SE242 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE242 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE242 :hasReference :R228 .
:SE242 :hasSideEffectDescription "Parosmia is an alternative word name for Impaired smell. It is the partial or total loss or abnormal perception of the sense of smell." .

:SE243 :hasReference :R229 .
:SE243 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE243 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE243 :hasSideEffectDescription "Myasthenia gravis, sometimes called MG, is a chronic (long-lasting) disease that causes weakness in your voluntary muscles. The voluntary muscles are the ones that you can control." .

:SE244 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE244 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE244 :hasReference :R230 .
:SE244 :hasSideEffectDescription "Blurred Vision is the loss of sharpness of vision and the inability to see fine details." .

:SE245 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE245 :hasReference :R231 .
:SE245 :hasSideEffectDescription "An ear disorder is a condition that may affect your hearing or balance." .
:SE245 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE246 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE246 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE246 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE246 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE247 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE247 :hasReference :R181 .
:SE247 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE247 :hasSideEffectDescription "Palpitations are feelings or sensations that your heart is pounding or racing. They can be felt in your chest, throat, or neck." .

:SE248 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE248 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hot flushes are sudden strong feelings of heat and sweating." .
:SE248 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE248 :hasReference :R232 .

:SE249 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE249 :hasReference :R161 .
:SE249 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE249 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspnea is shortness of breath." .

:SE250 :hasSideEffectDescription "Epistaxis is an alternative name of nose bleed. It is a loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose. Bleeding most often occurs from one nostril only." .
:SE250 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE250 :hasReference :R179 .
:SE250 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE251 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE251 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE251 :hasSideEffectDescription "Constipation means having fewer than three bowel movements a week. The stool (poop) can be hard and dry. Sometimes it is painful to pass. At one time or another, almost everyone gets constipated. In most cases, it lasts a short time and is not serious." .
:SE251 :hasReference :R162 .

:SE252 :hasReference :R213 .
:SE252 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE252 :hasSideEffectDescription "Flatulence is also called gas. Gas is air in the intestine that is passed through the rectum. Air that moves from the digestive tract through the mouth is called belching." .
:SE252 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE253 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .
:SE253 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE253 :hasReference :R164 .
:SE253 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE254 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE254 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE254 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastritis occurs when the lining of the stomach becomes inflamed or swollen. Gastritis may last for only a short time (acute gastritis) or it may linger for month to years (chronic gastritis)." .
:SE254 :hasReference :R187 .

:SE255 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE255 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysphagia is a term that means difficulty swallowing. Usually, when you swallow, food moves easily from your mouth, down your throat, and into your stomach." .
:SE255 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE255 :hasReference :R136 .

:SE256 :hasSideEffectDescription "Having dry mouth, also called xerostomia, means that you don't have enough saliva to keep your mouth wet. Everyone has a dry mouth once in a while, like when you are nervous or stressed. But if you have a dry mouth all or most of the time, it can be uncomfortable. It can make chewing, swallowing, and even talking difficult. It also raises your risk for tooth decay or infections in the mouth." .
:SE256 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE256 :hasReference :R233 .
:SE256 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE257 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE257 :hasReference :R213 .
:SE257 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE257 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eructation is also called Gas. It comes from two sources: air that you swallow and the breakdown of undigested food by bacteria in the large intestine. Certain foods may cause gas. Foods that produce gas in one person may not cause gas in another." .

:SE258 :hasReference :R234 .
:SE258 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE258 :hasSideEffectDescription "Mouth ulcers are sores or open lesions in the mouth." .
:SE258 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE259 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE259 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .
:SE259 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE259 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE260 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE260 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE260 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE260 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE261 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pruritus is an alternative name for Itching. It is a tingling or irritation of the skin that makes you want to scratch the area. Itching may occur all over the body or only in one location." .
:SE261 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE261 :hasReference :R166 .
:SE261 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE262 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE262 :hasReference :R141 .
:SE262 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE262 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .

:SE263 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dermatitis is also called Rashes. It is an  area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin. Rashes are a symptom of many different medical problems." .
:SE263 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE263 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE263 :hasReference :R165 .

:SE264 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE264 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dry skin occurs when your skin loses too much water and oil. Dry skin is common and can affect anyone at any age." .
:SE264 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE264 :hasReference :R235 .

:SE265 :hasReference :R236 .
:SE265 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE265 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE265 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hyperhidrosis is a medical condition in which a person sweats excessively and unpredictably. People with hyperhidrosis may sweat even when the temperature is cool or when they are at rest." .

:SE266 :hasPattern :Rare .
:SE266 :hasReference :R156 .
:SE266 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE266 :hasSideEffectDescription "Photosensitivity is an increased sensitivity to sunlight." .

:SE267 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .
:SE267 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE267 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE267 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE268 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE268 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Toxic Epidermal Necrolysis represents the more severe end." .
:SE268 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE268 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE269 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE269 :hasReference :R154 .
:SE269 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE269 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .

:SE270 :hasReference :R237 .
:SE270 :hasSideEffectDescription "Osteoarthritis, sometimes called OA, is a type of arthritis that only affects the joints, usually in the hands, knees, hips, neck, and lower back. It's the most common type of arthritis." .
:SE270 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE270 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE271 :hasSideEffectDescription "Back pain is one of the most common medical problems, affecting 8 out of 10 people at some point during their lives. Back pain can range from a dull, constant ache to a sudden, sharp pain. Most back pain goes away on its own, though it may take awhile." .
:SE271 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE271 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE271 :hasReference :R238 .

:SE272 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neck pain is discomfort in any of the structures in the neck. These include the muscles, nerves, bones (vertebrae), joints, and the discs between the bones." .
:SE272 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE272 :hasReference :R239 .
:SE272 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE273 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE273 :hasSideEffectDescription "Arthralgia is an alternative name of joint pain. It can affect one or more joints. Joint pain can be caused by many types of injuries or conditions. It may be linked to arthritis, bursitis, and muscle pain." .
:SE273 :hasReference :R191 .
:SE273 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE274 :hasReference :R240 .
:SE274 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysuria is an alternative name for painful urination. It is any pain, discomfort, or burning sensation when passing urine." .
:SE274 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE274 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE275 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE275 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE275 :hasSideEffectDescription "Acute Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .
:SE275 :hasReference :R192 .

:SE276 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE276 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nephritis is a kidney disorder in which the spaces between the kidney tubules become swollen (inflamed). This can cause problems with the way your kidneys work." .
:SE276 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE276 :hasReference :R217 .

:SE277 :hasReference :R241 .
:SE277 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE277 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE277 :hasSideEffectDescription "A testicular disorder is a condition where the testicles can get inflamed or infected, or develop cancer." .

:SE278 :hasSideEffectDescription "Edema means swelling caused by fluid in your body's tissues. It usually occurs in the feet, ankles and legs, but it can involve your entire body." .
:SE278 :hasReference :R168 .
:SE278 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE278 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE279 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE279 :hasSideEffectDescription "Malaise is a general feeling of discomfort, illness, or lack of well-being." .
:SE279 :hasReference :R242 .
:SE279 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE280 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE280 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE280 :hasSideEffectDescription "Fatigue is a feeling of weariness, tiredness, or lack of energy. It can interfere with your usual daily activities. Fatigue can be a normal response to physical activity, emotional stress, boredom, or lack of sleep." .
:SE280 :hasReference :R218 .

:SE281 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .
:SE281 :hasReference :R189 .
:SE281 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE281 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE282 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE282 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pyrexia is also called a fever. It is a body temperature that is higher than normal. A normal temperature can vary from person to person, but it is usually around 98.6 °F (37 °C). A fever is not a disease. It is usually a sign that your body is trying to fight an illness or infection." .
:SE282 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE282 :hasReference :R212 .

:SE283 :hasReference :R243 .
:SE283 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pain is a signal in your nervous system that something may be wrong. It is an unpleasant feeling, such as a prick, tingle, sting, burn, or ache. Each person feels pain differently, even if the reason for the pain is the same. Pain may be sharp or dull. It may be mild or severe. Pain may come and go, or it may be constant." .
:SE283 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE283 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE284 :hasReference :R151 .
:SE284 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE284 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE284 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .

:SE285 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE285 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE285 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .
:SE285 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE286 :hasSideEffectDescription "The aspartate aminotransferase (AST) blood test measures the level of the enzyme AST in the blood. Increased aspartate aminotransferase means an increased AST level in the blood." .
:SE286 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE286 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE286 :hasReference :R244 .

:SE287 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE287 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE287 :hasSideEffectDescription "Alanine aminotransferase (ALT) blood test measures the level of the enzyme ALT in the blood. Increased alanine aminotransferase means an increased ALT level in the blood." .
:SE287 :hasReference :R245 .

:SE288 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE288 :hasReference :R246 .
:SE288 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE288 :hasSideEffectDescription "Blood bilirubin increased means too much of a yellow substance in the blood." .

:SE289 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE289 :hasReference :R247 .
:SE289 :hasSideEffectDescription "Blood potassium level is a condition in which the amount of potassium in the blood is lower than normal." .
:SE289 :hasPattern :Uncommon .

:SE290 :hasReference :R248 .
:SE290 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE290 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE290 :hasSideEffectDescription "Increased glucose is a sign of high blood sugar." .

:SE291 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE291 :hasSideEffectDescription "Increased platelet is an increase in the platelet count which can increase the risk of blood clots." .
:SE291 :hasReference :R249 .
:SE291 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE292 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE292 :hasReference :R009 .
:SE292 :hasSideEffectDescription "Deafness can keep you from hearing sound at all" .
:SE292 :hasReference :R250 .

:SE293 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tinnitus is often described as a ringing in the ears. It also can sound like roaring, clicking, hissing, or buzzing. It may be soft or loud, high pitched or low pitched. You might hear it in either one or both ears." .
:SE293 :hasReference :R251 .
:SE293 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE293 :hasReference :R009 .

:SE294 :hasPattern :Serious .
:SE294 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioedema is a swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE294 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE294 :hasReference :R142 .

:SE295 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE295 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE295 :hasPattern :Serious .
:SE295 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE296 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE296 :hasPattern :Serious .
:SE296 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE296 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE297 :hasPattern :Serious .
:SE297 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE297 :hasReference :R13 .
:SE297 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .

:SE298 :hasPattern :Serious .
:SE298 :hasReference :R163 .
:SE298 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE298 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .

:SE299 :hasReference :R181 .
:SE299 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE299 :hasSideEffectDescription "Palpitations are feelings or sensations that your heart is pounding or racing. They can be felt in your chest, throat, or neck." .
:SE299 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE300 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE300 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .
:SE300 :hasReference :R189 .
:SE300 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE301 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .
:SE301 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE301 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE301 :hasReference :R164 .

:SE302 :hasReference :R213 .
:SE302 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE302 :hasSideEffectDescription "Flatulence is also called gas. Gas is air in the intestine that is passed through the rectum. Air that moves from the digestive tract through the mouth is called belching." .
:SE302 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE303 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE303 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE303 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE303 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE304 :hasSideEffectDescription "Black or tarry stools with a foul smell are a sign of a problem in the upper digestive tract. It most often indicates that there is bleeding in the esophagus, stomach, or first part of the small intestine. The term melena is used to describe this finding." .
:SE304 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE304 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE305 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE305 :hasReference :R193 .
:SE305 :hasSideEffectDescription "Moniliasis is also called yeast infections. It is a fungus that lives almost everywhere, including in your body. Usually, your immune system keeps yeast under control." .
:SE305 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE306 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginitis, also called vulvovaginitis, is an inflammation or infection of the vagina. It can also affect the vulva, which is the external part of a woman's genitals. Vaginitis can cause itching, pain, discharge, and odor." .
:SE306 :hasReference :R167 .
:SE306 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE306 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE307 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nephritis is a kidney disorder in which the spaces between the kidney tubules become swollen (inflamed). This can cause problems with the way your kidneys work." .
:SE307 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE307 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE307 :hasReference :R217 .

:SE308 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE308 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE308 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE308 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE309 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE309 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE309 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE309 :hasReference :R159 .

:SE310 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE310 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE310 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE310 :hasReference :R160 .

:SE311 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE311 :hasReference :R177 .
:SE311 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE311 :hasSideEffectDescription "Somnolence is an alternative name of drowsiness. It refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day." .

:SE312 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE312 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE312 :hasReference :R218 .
:SE312 :hasSideEffectDescription "Fatigue is a feeling of weariness, tiredness, or lack of energy. It can interfere with your usual daily activities. Fatigue can be a normal response to physical activity, emotional stress, boredom, or lack of sleep." .

:SE313 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE313 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE313 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE313 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE314 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE314 :hasSideEffectDescription "Photosensitivity is an increased sensitivity to sunlight." .
:SE314 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE314 :hasReference :R156 .

:SE315 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE315 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE315 :hasSideEffectDescription "Arthralgia is an alternative name of joint pain. It can affect one or more joints. Joint pain can be caused by many types of injuries or conditions. It may be linked to arthritis, bursitis, and muscle pain." .
:SE315 :hasReference :R191 .

:SE316 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE316 :hasReference :R168 .
:SE316 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE316 :hasSideEffectDescription "Edema means swelling caused by fluid in your body's tissues. It usually occurs in the feet, ankles and legs, but it can involve your entire body." .

:SE317 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE317 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE317 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE317 :hasReference :R141 .

:SE318 :hasSideEffectDescription "An arrhythmia is a problem with the rate or rhythm of your heartbeat. Your heart beats too quickly, too slowly, or with an irregular pattern. Changes in the electrical signals that control your heartbeat cause arrhythmias." .
:SE318 :hasReference :R216 .
:SE318 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE318 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE319 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE319 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE319 :hasReference :R182 .
:SE319 :hasSideEffectDescription "Ventricular tachycardia (VT) is a rapid heartbeat that starts in the lower chambers of the heart (ventricles)." .

:SE320 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE320 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE320 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .
:SE320 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE321 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypotension is also called as Low Blood Pressure. It is the force of your blood pushing against the walls of your arteries. Each time your heart beats, it pumps out blood into the arteries. Your blood pressure is highest when your heart beats, pumping the blood." .
:SE321 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE321 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE321 :hasReference :R183 .

:SE322 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE322 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE322 :hasSideEffectDescription "Constipation means having fewer than three bowel movements a week. The stool (poop) can be hard and dry. Sometimes it is painful to pass. At one time or another, almost everyone gets constipated. In most cases, it lasts a short time and is not serious." .
:SE322 :hasReference :R162 .

:SE323 :hasReference :R203 .
:SE323 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .
:SE323 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE323 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE324 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE324 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE324 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .
:SE324 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE325 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE325 :hasReference :R184 .
:SE325 :hasSideEffectDescription "Oral Candidiasis, commonly known as thrush, is a yeast infection of the mouth or throat." .
:SE325 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE326 :hasSideEffectDescription "Paresthesia is an alternative name of Numbness and Tingling. These are abnormal sensations that can occur anywhere in your body, but they are often felt in your fingers, hands, feet, arms, or legs." .
:SE326 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE326 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE326 :hasReference :R175 .

:SE327 :hasSideEffectDescription "Malaise is a general feeling of discomfort, illness, or lack of well-being." .
:SE327 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE327 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE327 :hasReference :R242 .

:SE328 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE328 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE328 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE328 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .

:SE329 :hasReference :R217 .
:SE329 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nephritis is a kidney disorder in which the spaces between the kidney tubules become swollen (inflamed). This can cause problems with the way your kidneys work." .
:SE329 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE329 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE330 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE330 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE330 :hasReference :R192 .
:SE330 :hasSideEffectDescription "Acute Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .

:SE331 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE331 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE331 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE331 :hasReference :R149 .

:SE332 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE332 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE332 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatitis is inflammation of the liver. Inflammation is swelling that happens when tissues of the body are injured or infected. It can damage your liver. This swelling and damage can affect how well your liver functions." .
:SE332 :hasReference :R251 .

:SE333 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE333 :hasReference :R199 .
:SE333 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE333 :hasSideEffectDescription "Convulsions can also be called as Seizures. These are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .

:SE334 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE334 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE334 :hasReference :R172 .
:SE334 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agitation is an unpleasant state of extreme arousal. An agitated person may feel stirred up, excited, tense, confused, or irritable." .

:SE335 :hasSideEffectDescription "Syncope is also called Fainting. It is a temporary loss of consciousness. If you're about to faint, you'll feel dizzy, lightheaded, or nauseous. Your field of vision may \"white out\" or \"black out.\" Your skin may be cold and clammy. You lose muscle control at the same time, and may fall down." .
:SE335 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE335 :hasReference :R178 .
:SE335 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE336 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE336 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE336 :hasReference :R171 .
:SE336 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anxiety is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness. It might cause you to sweat, feel restless and tense, and have a rapid heartbeat. It can be a normal reaction to stress." .

:SE337 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pruritus is an alternative name for Itching. It is a tingling or irritation of the skin that makes you want to scratch the area. Itching may occur all over the body or only in one location." .
:SE337 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE337 :hasReference :R166 .
:SE337 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE338 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .
:SE338 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE338 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE338 :hasReference :R154 .

:SE339 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE339 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE339 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE339 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .

:SE340 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE340 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Toxic Epidermal Necrolysis represents the more severe end." .
:SE340 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE340 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE341 :hasReference :R250 .
:SE341 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE341 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE341 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hearing loss means hearing disorders make it hard, but not impossible, to hear." .

:SE342 :hasReference :R010 .
:SE342 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE342 :hasReference :R250 .
:SE342 :hasSideEffectDescription "Deafness can keep you from hearing sound at all" .

:SE343 :hasReference :R251 .
:SE343 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE343 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tinnitus is often described as a ringing in the ears. It also can sound like roaring, clicking, hissing, or buzzing. It may be soft or loud, high pitched or low pitched. You might hear it in either one or both ears." .
:SE343 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE344 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE344 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE344 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE344 :hasReference :R010 .

:SE345 :hasSideEffectDescription "Leukopenia is a low white blood count." .
:SE345 :hasReference :R224 .
:SE345 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE345 :hasReference :R011 .

:SE346 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE346 :hasReference :R147 .
:SE346 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE346 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .

:SE347 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE347 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioneurotic Edema's alternative name is Angioedema. It is swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE347 :hasReference :R142 .
:SE347 :hasPattern :VeryRare .

:SE348 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE348 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE348 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE348 :hasPattern :VeryRare .

:SE349 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .
:SE349 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE349 :hasReference :R144 .
:SE349 :hasReference :R011 .

:SE350 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE350 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE350 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypersensitivity vasculitis is an extreme reaction to a medicine, infection, or foreign substance. It leads to inflammation and damage to blood vessels, mainly in the skin. The term is not used much currently because more specific names are considered more precise." .
:SE350 :hasReference :R253 .

:SE351 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE351 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE351 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE351 :hasReference :R011 .

:SE352 :hasSideEffectDescription "Convulsions can also be called as Seizures. These are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .
:SE352 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE352 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE352 :hasReference :R199 .

:SE353 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE353 :hasReference :R254 .
:SE353 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE353 :hasSideEffectDescription "Mucocutaneous candidiasis is a pattern of recurrent and persistent infections of the skin, the nails, and the moist lining of body cavities (mucous membranes)." .

:SE354 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE354 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE354 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE354 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE355 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE355 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE355 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE355 :hasReference :R133 .

:SE356 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE356 :hasPattern :Uncommon .
:SE356 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE356 :hasReference :R011 .

:SE357 :hasSideEffectDescription "Black hairy tongue is produced when the papilla (finger-like projections from the surface of the tongue) fail to fall off as they normally do. As the length of the papilla increase, debris collects and bacteria grow, producing the characteristic dark \"furry\" appearance." .
:SE357 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE357 :hasPattern :VeryRare .
:SE357 :hasReference :R255 .

:SE358 :hasReference :R011 .
:SE358 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE358 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE358 :hasReference :R165 .

