:SE411 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea, dyspepsia, abdominal pain, vomiting, and diarrhea are the most frequent adverse effects of Clarithromycin but are usually mild and less frequent than with erythromycin." .
:SE411 :hasReference :R014 .

:SE412 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stomatitis is a viral infection of the mouth that causes sores and ulcers. These mouth ulcers are not the same as canker sores, which are not caused by a virus." .
:SE412 :hasReference :R188 .
:SE412 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE412 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE413 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE413 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE413 :hasReference :R135 .
:SE413 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .

:SE414 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE414 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE414 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tooth discoloration is any color other than white to yellowish-white." .
:SE414 :hasReference :R258 .

:SE415 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE415 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatitis is inflammation of the liver. Inflammation is swelling that happens when tissues of the body are injured or infected. It can damage your liver. This swelling and damage can affect how well your liver functions." .
:SE415 :hasReference :R252 .
:SE415 :hasReference :R014 .

:SE416 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE416 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE416 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE416 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE417 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE417 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE417 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE417 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE418 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE418 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE418 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE418 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .

:SE419 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE419 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE419 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anxiety is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness. It might cause you to sweat, feel restless and tense, and have a rapid heartbeat. It can be a normal reaction to stress." .
:SE419 :hasReference :R171 .

:SE420 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE420 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE420 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE420 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE421 :hasReference :R158 .
:SE421 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE421 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE421 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .

:SE422 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE422 :hasReference :R196 .
:SE422 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE422 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hallucinations involve sensing things such as visions, sounds, or smells that seem real but are not. These things are created by the mind." .

:SE423 :hasSideEffectDescription "Confusion is the inability to think as clearly or quickly as you normally do. You may feel disoriented and have difficulty paying attention, remembering, and making decisions." .
:SE423 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE423 :hasReference :R173 .
:SE423 :hasReference :R014 .

:SE424 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hearing loss means hearing disorders make it hard, but not impossible, to hear." .
:SE424 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE424 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE424 :hasReference :R250 .

:SE425 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypoglycemia means low glucose. It happens when the level of glucose in your blood drops below what is healthy for you." .
:SE425 :hasReference :R170 .
:SE425 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE425 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE426 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE426 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE426 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE426 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .

:SE427 :hasPattern :Rare .
:SE427 :hasReference :R217 .
:SE427 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nephritis is a kidney disorder in which the spaces between the kidney tubules become swollen (inflamed). This can cause problems with the way your kidneys work." .
:SE427 :hasReference :R014 .

:SE428 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE428 :hasSideEffectDescription "Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .
:SE428 :hasReference :R192 .
:SE428 :hasPattern :Rare .

:SE429 :hasReference :R203 .
:SE429 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .
:SE429 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE429 :hasReference :R014 .

:SE430 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE430 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .
:SE430 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE430 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE431 :hasSideEffectDescription "A fever is a body temperature that is higher than normal. A normal temperature can vary from person to person, but it is usually around 98.6 °F (37 °C). A fever is not a disease. It is usually a sign that your body is trying to fight an illness or infection." .
:SE431 :hasReference :R014 .
:SE431 :hasReference :R212 .
:SE431 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE432 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE432 :hasReference :R015 .
:SE432 :hasReference :R211 .
:SE432 :hasSideEffectDescription "Rhabdomyolysis is the breakdown of muscle tissue that leads to the release of muscle fiber contents into the blood. These substances are harmful to the kidney and often cause kidney damage." .

:SE433 :hasReference :R134 .
:SE433 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE433 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE433 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .

:SE434 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE434 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE434 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE434 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE435 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE435 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE435 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE435 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE436 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE436 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE436 :hasReference :R164 .
:SE436 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .

:SE437 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE437 :hasReference :R163 .
:SE437 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE437 :hasPattern :Common .

:SE438 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE438 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE438 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE438 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE439 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE439 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE439 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE439 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE440 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE440 :hasReference :R193 .
:SE440 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE440 :hasSideEffectDescription "Candidiasis is also called Yeast Infections.  It is a fungus that lives almost everywhere, including in your body. Usually, your immune system keeps yeast under control." .

:SE441 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE441 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE441 :hasReference :R259 .
:SE441 :hasSideEffectDescription "Cellulitis is an infection of the skin and deep underlying tissues. Group A strep (streptococcal) bacteria are the most common cause. The bacteria enter your body when you get an injury such as a bruise, burn, surgical cut, or wound." .

:SE442 :hasReference :R260 .
:SE442 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE442 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erysipelas is a type of skin infection. It affects the outermost layer of the skin and the local lymph nodes." .
:SE442 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE443 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE443 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE443 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythrasma is a long-term skin infection caused by a specific bacteria. It commonly occurs in skin folds." .
:SE443 :hasReference :R261 .

:SE444 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE444 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE444 :hasReference :R203 .
:SE444 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .

:SE445 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE445 :hasSideEffectDescription "Rhinitis is a condition that includes a runny nose, sneezing, and nasal stuffiness. When environmental allergies (such as hay fever) or a cold are not causing these symptoms, the condition is called nonallergic rhinitis." .
:SE445 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE445 :hasReference :R223 .

:SE446 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginal Infection is an infection of the vagina. It is most often due to the fungus. Most women have a vaginal yeast infection at some time." .
:SE446 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE446 :hasReference :R215 .
:SE446 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE447 :hasReference :R190 .
:SE447 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE447 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anemia is also called iron poor blood. Anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE447 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE448 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE448 :hasReference :R256 .
:SE448 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agranulocytosis is when the body has too few granulocytes." .
:SE448 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE449 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE449 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE449 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE449 :hasReference :R151 .

:SE450 :hasSideEffectDescription "Leukopenia is a low white blood count." .
:SE450 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE450 :hasReference :R224 .
:SE450 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE451 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE451 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE451 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE451 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .

:SE452 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE452 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE452 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE452 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE453 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylactoid Reaction is an anaphylactic-like reaction." .
:SE453 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE453 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE453 :hasReference :R143 .

:SE454 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE454 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE454 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE454 :hasReference :R143 .

:SE455 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioedema is a swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE455 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE455 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE455 :hasReference :R142 .

:SE456 :hasReference :R225 .
:SE456 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypersensitivity is also called Allergy. It is a reaction by your immune system to something that does not bother most other people. People who have allergies often are sensitive to more than one thing" .
:SE456 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE456 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE457 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE457 :hasSideEffectDescription "Myasthenia gravis, sometimes called MG, is a chronic (long-lasting) disease that causes weakness in your voluntary muscles. The voluntary muscles are the ones that you can control." .
:SE457 :hasReference :R229 .
:SE457 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE458 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .
:SE458 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE458 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE458 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE459 :hasSideEffectDescription "A decreased appetite is when your desire to eat is reduced. The medical term for a loss of appetite is anorexia." .
:SE459 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE459 :hasReference :R257 .
:SE459 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE460 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypoglycemia means low glucose. It happens when the level of glucose in your blood drops below what is healthy for you." .
:SE460 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE460 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE460 :hasReference :R170 .

:SE461 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anxiety is a feeling of fear, dread, and uneasiness. It might cause you to sweat, feel restless and tense, and have a rapid heartbeat. It can be a normal reaction to stress." .
:SE461 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE461 :hasReference :R171 .
:SE461 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE462 :hasReference :R173 .
:SE462 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE462 :hasSideEffectDescription "Confusion is the inability to think as clearly or quickly as you normally do. You may feel disoriented and have difficulty paying attention, remembering, and making decisions." .
:SE462 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE463 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE463 :hasReference :R195 .
:SE463 :hasSideEffectDescription "Depression is more than a feeling of being sad or irritable for a few days. It's a serious mood disorder." .
:SE463 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE464 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE464 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hallucinations involve sensing things such as visions, sounds, or smells that seem real but are not. These things are created by the mind." .
:SE464 :hasReference :R196 .
:SE464 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE465 :hasReference :R158 .
:SE465 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE465 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE465 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .

:SE466 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE466 :hasSideEffectDescription "A nightmare is a bad dream that brings out strong feelings of fear, terror, distress, or anxiety." .
:SE466 :hasReference :R197 .
:SE466 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE467 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE467 :hasReference :R262 .
:SE467 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE467 :hasSideEffectDescription "Psychotic disorders are severe mental disorders that cause abnormal thinking and perceptions. People with psychoses lose touch with reality." .

:SE468 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE468 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anosmia is when the sense of smell is completely absent." .
:SE468 :hasReference :R227 .
:SE468 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE469 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE469 :hasReference :R199 .
:SE469 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE469 :hasSideEffectDescription "Convulsions can also be called as Seizures. These are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .

:SE470 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE470 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE470 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE470 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE471 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyskinesia means abnormal movement." .
:SE471 :hasReference :R263 .
:SE471 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE471 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE472 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE472 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE472 :hasSideEffectDescription "Loss of Consciousness is an alternative name for Unconsciousness. It is when a person is unable to respond to people and activities." .
:SE472 :hasReference :R264 .

:SE473 :hasSideEffectDescription "Asthma is a chronic (long-term) lung disease. It affects your airways, the tubes that carry air in and out of your lungs. When you have asthma, your airways can become inflamed and narrowed. This can cause wheezing, coughing, and tightness in your chest. When these symptoms get worse than usual, it is called an asthma attack or flare-up." .
:SE473 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE473 :hasReference :R265 .
:SE473 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE474 :hasReference :R266 .
:SE474 :hasSideEffectDescription "Coughing is a reflex that keeps your throat and airways clear. Although it can be annoying, coughing helps your body heal or protect itself." .
:SE474 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE474 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE475 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE475 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspnea is shortness of breath." .
:SE475 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE475 :hasReference :R161 .

:SE476 :hasSideEffectDescription "Epistaxis is an alternative name of nose bleed. It is a loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose. Bleeding most often occurs from one nostril only." .
:SE476 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE476 :hasReference :R179 .
:SE476 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE477 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE477 :hasReference :R222 .
:SE477 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pharyngitis, or sore throat, is discomfort, pain, or scratchiness in the throat. It often makes it painful to swallow." .
:SE477 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE478 :hasReference :R267 .
:SE478 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE478 :hasSideEffectDescription "A pulmonary embolism (PE) is a sudden blockage in a lung artery. It usually happens when a blood clot breaks loose and travels through the bloodstream to the lungs." .
:SE478 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE479 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE479 :hasSideEffectDescription "Constipation means having fewer than three bowel movements a week. The stool (poop) can be hard and dry. Sometimes it is painful to pass. At one time or another, almost everyone gets constipated. In most cases, it lasts a short time and is not serious." .
:SE479 :hasReference :R162 .
:SE479 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE480 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE480 :hasReference :R214 .
:SE480 :hasSideEffectDescription "Black or tarry stools with a foul smell are a sign of a problem in the upper digestive tract. It most often indicates that there is bleeding in the esophagus, stomach, or first part of the small intestine." .
:SE480 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE481 :hasSideEffectDescription "Having dry mouth, also called xerostomia, means that you don't have enough saliva to keep your mouth wet. Everyone has a dry mouth once in a while, like when you are nervous or stressed. But if you have a dry mouth all or most of the time, it can be uncomfortable. It can make chewing, swallowing, and even talking difficult. It also raises your risk for tooth decay or infections in the mouth." .
:SE481 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE481 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE481 :hasReference :R233 .

:SE482 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE482 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE482 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eructation is also called Gas. It comes from two sources: air that you swallow and the breakdown of undigested food by bacteria in the large intestine. Certain foods may cause gas. Foods that produce gas in one person may not cause gas in another." .
:SE482 :hasReference :R213 .

:SE483 :hasReference :R137 .
:SE483 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE483 :hasSideEffectDescription "Esophagitis is a condition in which the lining of the esophagus becomes swollen, inflamed, or irritated. The esophagus is the tube that leads from your mouth to the stomach." .
:SE483 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE484 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE484 :hasReference :R213 .
:SE484 :hasSideEffectDescription "Flatulence is also called gas. Gas is air in the intestine that is passed through the rectum. Air that moves from the digestive tract through the mouth is called belching." .
:SE484 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE485 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE485 :hasReference :R187 .
:SE485 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastritis occurs when the lining of the stomach becomes inflamed or swollen. Gastritis may last for only a short time (acute gastritis) or it may linger for month to years (chronic gastritis)." .
:SE485 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE486 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE486 :hasSideEffectDescription "Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease is a chronic (long-lasting) condition that can cause discomfort and, over time, lead to other health problems." .
:SE486 :hasReference :R268 .
:SE486 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE487 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE487 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE487 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE487 :hasReference :R135 .

:SE488 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE488 :hasSideEffectDescription "Oral Candidiasis, commonly known as thrush, is a yeast infection of the mouth or throat." .
:SE488 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE488 :hasReference :R184 .

:SE489 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancreatitis is inflammation of the pancreas. It happens when digestive enzymes start digesting the pancreas itself. Pancreatitis can be acute or chronic. Either form is serious and can lead to complications." .
:SE489 :hasReference :R152 .
:SE489 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE489 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE490 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE490 :hasReference :R188 .
:SE490 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE490 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stomatitis is a viral infection of the mouth that causes sores and ulcers. These mouth ulcers are not the same as canker sores, which are not caused by a virus." .

:SE491 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tooth discoloration is any color other than white to yellowish-white." .
:SE491 :hasReference :R258 .
:SE491 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE491 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE492 :hasReference :R269 .
:SE492 :hasSideEffectDescription "Cholestasis is any condition in which the flow of bile from the liver is slowed or blocked." .
:SE492 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE492 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE493 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE493 :hasSideEffectDescription "Jaundice causes your skin and the whites of your eyes to turn yellow. Too much bilirubin causes jaundice. Bilirubin is a yellow chemical in hemoglobin, the substance that carries oxygen in your red blood cells." .
:SE493 :hasReference :R270 .
:SE493 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE494 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE494 :hasReference :R252 .
:SE494 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE494 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatitis is inflammation of the liver. Inflammation is swelling that happens when tissues of the body are injured or infected. It can damage your liver. This swelling and damage can affect how well your liver functions." .

:SE495 :hasSideEffectDescription "Acne is a common skin disease that causes pimples. Pimples form when hair follicles under your skin clog up. Most pimples form on the face, neck, back, chest, and shoulders. Anyone can get acne, but it is common in teenagers and young adults. It is not serious, but it can cause scars." .
:SE495 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE495 :hasReference :R271 .
:SE495 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE496 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE496 :hasSideEffectDescription "area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin. Rashes are a symptom of many different medical problems." .
:SE496 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE496 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE497 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE497 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .
:SE497 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE497 :hasReference :R153 .

:SE498 :hasReference :R272 .
:SE498 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE498 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hematuria is having blood in your urine." .
:SE498 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE499 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE499 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE499 :hasReference :R217 .
:SE499 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nephritis is a kidney disorder in which the spaces between the kidney tubules become swollen (inflamed). This can cause problems with the way your kidneys work." .

:SE500 :hasReference :R192 .
:SE500 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE500 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE500 :hasSideEffectDescription "Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .

:SE501 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE501 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dysmenorrhea is also called as period pain. The pain is most often menstrual cramps, which are a throbbing, cramping pain in your lower abdomen. You may also have other symptoms, such as lower back pain, nausea, diarrhea, and headaches." .
:SE501 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE501 :hasReference :R273 .

:SE502 :hasReference :R218 .
:SE502 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE502 :hasReference :R016 .
:SE502 :hasSideEffectDescription "Fatigue is a feeling of weariness, tiredness, or lack of energy. It can interfere with your usual daily activities. Fatigue can be a normal response to physical activity, emotional stress, boredom, or lack of sleep." .

:SE503 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE503 :hasReference :R212 .
:SE503 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pyrexia is also called a fever. It is a body temperature that is higher than normal. A normal temperature can vary from person to person, but it is usually around 98.6 °F (37 °C). A fever is not a disease. It is usually a sign that your body is trying to fight an illness or infection." .
:SE503 :hasReference :R016 .

:SE504 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE504 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE504 :hasReference :R017 .
:SE504 :hasReference :R133 .

:SE505 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE505 :hasReference :R017 .
:SE505 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE505 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE506 :hasReference :R017 .
:SE506 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .
:SE506 :hasPattern :Common .
:SE506 :hasReference :R164 .

:SE507 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE507 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
