:SE546 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .
:SE546 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE547 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE547 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE547 :hasReference :R147 .
:SE547 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE548 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE548 :hasSideEffectDescription "Leukopenia is a low white blood count." .
:SE548 :hasReference :R224 .
:SE548 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE549 :hasReference :R205 .
:SE549 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE549 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancytopenia can result in extreme tiredness (fatigue) due to low numbers of red blood cells (anemia), frequent infections due to low numbers of white blood cells (neutropenia), and abnormal bleeding due to low numbers of platelets (thrombocytopenia)" .
:SE549 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE550 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE550 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE550 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE550 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE551 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE551 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE551 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatitis is inflammation of the liver. Inflammation is swelling that happens when tissues of the body are injured or infected. It can damage your liver. This swelling and damage can affect how well your liver functions." .
:SE551 :hasReference :R252 .

:SE552 :hasSideEffectDescription "Jaundice causes your skin and the whites of your eyes to turn yellow. Too much bilirubin causes jaundice. Bilirubin is a yellow chemical in hemoglobin, the substance that carries oxygen in your red blood cells." .
:SE552 :hasReference :R270 .
:SE552 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE552 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE553 :hasReference :R199 .
:SE553 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE553 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE553 :hasSideEffectDescription "Seizures are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .

:SE554 :hasReference :R209 .
:SE554 :hasSideEffectDescription "Encephalopathy is an abnormal brain function." .
:SE554 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE554 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE555 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE555 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .
:SE555 :hasReference :R154 .
:SE555 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE556 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE556 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE556 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .
:SE556 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE557 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Toxic Epidermal Necrolysis represents the more severe end." .
:SE557 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE557 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE557 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

