:SE559 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE559 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemorrhage is also called Bleeding. It is the loss of blood. It can be external, or outside the body, like when you get a cut or wound. It can also be internal, or inside the body, like when you have an injury to an internal organ." .

:SE560 :hasSideEffectDescription "A BUN, or blood urea nitrogen test, measures the amount of urea nitrogen in your blood. Urea nitrogen is a waste product that forms as your body breaks down proteins. It's carried in your blood and then removed by your kidneys when you urinate (pee)." .
:SE560 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE560 :hasReference :R140 .
:SE560 :hasReference :R021 .

:SE561 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE561 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .
:SE561 :hasReference :R021 .
:SE561 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE562 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agranulocytosis is when the body has too few granulocytes." .
:SE562 :hasReference :R256 .
