:SE602 :hasReference :R141 .
:SE602 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE602 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE603 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE603 :hasReference :R023 .
:SE603 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE603 :hasReference :R151 .

:SE604 :hasReference :R212 .
:SE604 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE604 :hasReference :R023 .
:SE604 :hasSideEffectDescription "A fever is a body temperature that is higher than normal. A normal temperature can vary from person to person, but it is usually around 98.6 °F (37 °C). A fever is not a disease. It is usually a sign that your body is trying to fight an illness or infection." .

:SE605 :hasReference :R023 .
:SE605 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE605 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .
:SE605 :hasReference :R144 .

:SE606 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE606 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE606 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE606 :hasReference :R023 .

:SE607 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE607 :hasReference :R278 .
:SE607 :hasReference :R023 .
:SE607 :hasSideEffectDescription "The Coombs test looks for antibodies that may stick to your red blood cells and cause red blood cells to die too early." .

:SE608 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE608 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE608 :hasReference :R023 .
:SE608 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .

:SE609 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE609 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE609 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE609 :hasReference :R023 .

:SE610 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE610 :hasReference :R256 .
:SE610 :hasReference :R023 .
:SE610 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agranulocytosis is when the body has too few granulocytes." .

:SE611 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE611 :hasReference :R134 .
:SE611 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE611 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .

:SE612 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE612 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE612 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE612 :hasReference :R133 .

:SE613 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE613 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE613 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE613 :hasReference :R163 .

:SE614 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE614 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE614 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE614 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE615 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE615 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE615 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE615 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .

:SE616 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE616 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE616 :hasSideEffectDescription "Restlessness is an alternative name for agitation. It is an unpleasant state of extreme arousal. An agitated person may feel stirred up, excited, tense, confused, or irritable." .
:SE616 :hasReference :R172 .

:SE617 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE617 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE617 :hasReference :R024 .
:SE617 :hasReference :R160 .

:SE618 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE618 :hasReference :R185 .
:SE618 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatic lipase deficiency is a disorder that affects the body's ability to break down fats (lipids). People with this disorder have increased amounts of certain fats, known as triglycerides and cholesterol, in the blood." .
:SE618 :hasReference :R024 .

:SE619 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE619 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE619 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE619 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE620 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE620 :hasReference :R134 .
:SE620 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE620 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .

:SE621 :hasReference :R163 .
:SE621 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE621 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE621 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE622 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE622 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE622 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE622 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .

:SE623 :hasSideEffectDescription "Restlessness is an alternative name for agitation. It is an unpleasant state of extreme arousal. An agitated person may feel stirred up, excited, tense, confused, or irritable." .
:SE623 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE623 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE623 :hasReference :R172 .

:SE624 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE624 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE624 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .
:SE624 :hasReference :R165 .

:SE625 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE625 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .
:SE625 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE625 :hasReference :R025 .

:SE626 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE626 :hasReference :R164 .
:SE626 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE626 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .

:SE627 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE627 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .
:SE627 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE627 :hasReference :R025 .

:SE628 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE628 :hasSideEffectDescription "Confusion is the inability to think as clearly or quickly as you normally do. You may feel disoriented and have difficulty paying attention, remembering, and making decisions." .
:SE628 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE628 :hasReference :R173 .

:SE629 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE629 :hasReference :R158 .
:SE629 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE629 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .

:SE630 :hasSideEffectDescription "A tremor is a neurological condition that includes shaking or trembling movements in one or more parts of your body. It most often affects the hands. But it can also affect the arms, legs, head, vocal cords, and torso (trunk). A tremor is involuntary, meaning that you cannot control it. It happens because of muscle contractions." .
:SE630 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE630 :hasReference :R174 .
:SE630 :hasReference :R025 .

:SE631 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE631 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE631 :hasSideEffectDescription "Drowsiness refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day. People who are drowsy may fall asleep when they do not want to or at times which can lead to safety concerns." .
:SE631 :hasReference :R177 .

:SE632 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE632 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE632 :hasSideEffectDescription "A nightmare is a bad dream that brings out strong feelings of fear, terror, distress, or anxiety." .
:SE632 :hasReference :R197 .

:SE633 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hallucinations involve sensing things such as visions, sounds, or smells that seem real but are not. These things are created by the mind." .
:SE633 :hasReference :R196 .
:SE633 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE633 :hasReference :R025 .

:SE634 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE634 :hasReference :R262 .
:SE634 :hasSideEffectDescription "Psychotic disorders are severe mental disorders that cause abnormal thinking and perceptions. People with psychoses lose touch with reality." .
:SE634 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE635 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE635 :hasSideEffectDescription "Depression is more than a feeling of being sad or irritable for a few days. It's a serious mood disorder." .
:SE635 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE635 :hasReference :R195 .

:SE636 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE636 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE636 :hasSideEffectDescription "Convulsions can also be called as Seizures. These are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .
:SE636 :hasReference :R199 .

:SE637 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE637 :hasSideEffectDescription "Intracranial Hypertension is a rise in the pressure inside the skull that can result from or cause brain injury." .
:SE637 :hasReference :R025 .
:SE637 :hasReference :R157 .

