:SE698 :hasReference :R144 .
:SE698 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE698 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .

:SE699 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE699 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE699 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Stevens-Johnson Syndrome represents the less severe end of the disease spectrum." .
:SE699 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE700 :hasReference :R153 .
:SE700 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE700 :hasSideEffectDescription "Stevens-Johnson syndrome/toxic epidermal necrolysis (SJS/TEN) is a severe skin reaction most often triggered by particular medications. Although Stevens-Johnson syndrome and toxic epidermal necrolysis were once thought to be separate conditions, they are now considered part of a continuum. Toxic Epidermal Necrolysis represents the more severe end." .
:SE700 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE701 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE701 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE701 :hasReference :R141 .
:SE701 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE702 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE702 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hepatitis is inflammation of the liver. Inflammation is swelling that happens when tissues of the body are injured or infected. It can damage your liver. This swelling and damage can affect how well your liver functions." .
:SE702 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE702 :hasReference :R252 .

:SE703 :hasReference :R270 .
:SE703 :hasSideEffectDescription "Jaundice causes your skin and the whites of your eyes to turn yellow. Too much bilirubin causes jaundice. Bilirubin is a yellow chemical in hemoglobin, the substance that carries oxygen in your red blood cells." .
:SE703 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE703 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE704 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE704 :hasSideEffectDescription "A BUN, or blood urea nitrogen test, measures the amount of urea nitrogen in your blood. Urea nitrogen is a waste product that forms as your body breaks down proteins. It's carried in your blood and then removed by your kidneys when you urinate (pee)." .
:SE704 :hasReference :R140 .
:SE704 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE705 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE705 :hasSideEffectDescription "Acute Renal Failure is an alternative name of Acute Kidney Failure. It is the rapid (less than 2 days) loss of your kidneys' ability to remove waste and help balance fluids and electrolytes in your body." .
:SE705 :hasReference :R192 .
:SE705 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE706 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE706 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE706 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginitis, also called vulvovaginitis, is an inflammation or infection of the vagina. It can also affect the vulva, which is the external part of a woman's genitals. Vaginitis can cause itching, pain, discharge, and odor." .
:SE706 :hasReference :R167 .

:SE707 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vaginal Infection is an infection of the vagina. It is most often due to the fungus. Most women have a vaginal yeast infection at some time." .
:SE707 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE707 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE707 :hasReference :R215 .

:SE708 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE708 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE708 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE708 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .

:SE709 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE709 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE709 :hasReference :R159 .
:SE709 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE710 :hasReference :R218 .
:SE710 :hasSideEffectDescription "Fatigue is a feeling of weariness, tiredness, or lack of energy. It can interfere with your usual daily activities. Fatigue can be a normal response to physical activity, emotional stress, boredom, or lack of sleep." .
:SE710 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE710 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE711 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE711 :hasSideEffectDescription "Insomnia is trouble falling asleep, staying asleep (usually through the night), or waking up too early in the morning. Episodes of insomnia may come and go or be long-lasting." .
:SE711 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE711 :hasReference :R158 .

:SE712 :hasReference :R242 .
:SE712 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE712 :hasSideEffectDescription "Malaise is a general feeling of discomfort, illness, or lack of well-being." .
:SE712 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE713 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE713 :hasSideEffectDescription "Seizures are symptoms of a brain problem. They happen because of sudden, abnormal electrical activity in the brain. When people think of seizures, they often think of convulsions in which a person's body shakes rapidly and uncontrollably." .
:SE713 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE713 :hasReference :R199 .

:SE714 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE714 :hasSideEffectDescription "Somnolence is an alternative name of drowsiness. It refers to feeling more sleepy than normal during the day." .
:SE714 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE714 :hasReference :R177 .

:SE715 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE715 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE715 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE715 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE716 :hasReference :R224 .
:SE716 :hasSideEffectDescription "Leukopenia is a low white blood count." .
:SE716 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE716 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE717 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE717 :hasReference :R150 .
:SE717 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE717 :hasSideEffectDescription "Neutropenia is a condition that increases the risk of repeated infections in affected individuals. People with this condition have an abnormally low level (deficiency) of neutrophils, a type of white blood cell that plays a role in inflammation and in fighting infection." .

:SE718 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE718 :hasReference :R256 .
:SE718 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE718 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agranulocytosis is when the body has too few granulocytes." .

:SE719 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE719 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE719 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE719 :hasReference :R151 .

:SE720 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE720 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE720 :hasSideEffectDescription "Immune hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide the oxygen to the body's tissue." .
:SE720 :hasReference :R148 .

:SE721 :hasReference :R161 .
:SE721 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE721 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspnea is shortness of breath." .
:SE721 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE722 :hasReference :R277 .
:SE722 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE722 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE722 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chills refers to feeling cold after being in a cold environment. The word can also refer to an episode of shivering along with paleness and feeling cold." .

:SE723 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hypotension is also called as Low Blood Pressure. It is the force of your blood pushing against the walls of your arteries. Each time your heart beats, it pumps out blood into the arteries. Your blood pressure is highest when your heart beats, pumping the blood." .
:SE723 :hasReference :R183 .
:SE723 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE723 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE724 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE724 :hasReference :R269 .
:SE724 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE724 :hasSideEffectDescription "Cholestasis is any condition in which the flow of bile from the liver is slowed or blocked." .

:SE725 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE725 :hasSideEffectDescription "Aplastic anemia is a rare but serious blood disorder. If you have it, your bone marrow doesn't make enough new blood cells. It happens when there is damage to stem cells inside your bone marrow." .
:SE725 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE725 :hasReference :R274 .

:SE726 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE726 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE726 :hasReference :R179 .
:SE726 :hasSideEffectDescription "Epistaxis is an alternative name of nose bleed. It is a loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose. Bleeding most often occurs from one nostril only." .

:SE727 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE727 :hasReference :R283 .
:SE727 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE727 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tenesmus is the feeling that you need to pass stools, even though your bowels are already empty. It may involve straining, pain, and cramping." .

:SE728 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE728 :hasReference :R135 .
:SE728 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .
:SE728 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE729 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE729 :hasReference :R184 .
:SE729 :hasSideEffectDescription "Oral Candidiasis, commonly known as thrush, is a yeast infection of the mouth or throat." .
:SE729 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE730 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE730 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE730 :hasSideEffectDescription "Heartburn is a painful burning feeling in your chest or throat. It happens when stomach acid backs up into your esophagus, the tube that carries food from your mouth to your stomach." .
:SE730 :hasReference :R284 .

:SE731 :hasReference :R197 .
:SE731 :hasSideEffectDescription "A nightmare is a bad dream that brings out strong feelings of fear, terror, distress, or anxiety." .
:SE731 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE731 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE732 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE732 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE732 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE732 :hasReference :R027 .

:SE733 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE733 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE733 :hasReference :R189 .
:SE733 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .

:SE734 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE734 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE734 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pleural Effusion is an excess fluid in the pleural space." .
:SE734 :hasReference :R285 .

:SE735 :hasReference :R266 .
:SE735 :hasSideEffectDescription "Coughing is a reflex that keeps your throat and airways clear. Although it can be annoying, coughing helps your body heal or protect itself." .
:SE735 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE735 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE736 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE736 :hasSideEffectDescription "Rhinitis is a condition that includes a runny nose, sneezing, and nasal stuffiness. When environmental allergies (such as hay fever) or a cold are not causing these symptoms, the condition is called nonallergic rhinitis." .
:SE736 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE736 :hasReference :R223 .

:SE737 :hasReference :R278 .
:SE737 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE737 :hasSideEffectDescription "The Coombs test looks for antibodies that may stick to your red blood cells and cause red blood cells to die too early." .
:SE737 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE738 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE738 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancytopenia can result in extreme tiredness (fatigue) due to low numbers of red blood cells (anemia), frequent infections due to low numbers of white blood cells (neutropenia), and abnormal bleeding due to low numbers of platelets (thrombocytopenia)" .
:SE738 :hasReference :R027 .
:SE738 :hasReference :R205 .

:SE739 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE739 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE739 :hasReference :R028 .

:SE740 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE740 :hasSideEffectDescription "Headache is the most common form of pain. It's a major reason people miss days at work or school or visit the doctor." .
:SE740 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE740 :hasReference :R159 .

:SE741 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE741 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE741 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE741 :hasSideEffectDescription "When you're dizzy, you may feel lightheaded, woozy, or disoriented. Diziness usually gets better by itself or is easily treated." .

:SE742 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE742 :hasReference :R165 .
:SE742 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE742 :hasSideEffectDescription "A rash is an area of irritated or swollen skin. Many rashes are itchy, red, painful, and irritated. Some rashes can also lead to blisters or patches of raw skin." .

:SE743 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE743 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pruritus is an alternative name for Itching. It is a tingling or irritation of the skin that makes you want to scratch the area. Itching may occur all over the body or only in one location." .
:SE743 :hasReference :R166 .
:SE743 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE744 :hasReference :R141 .
:SE744 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE744 :hasSideEffectDescription "Urticaria is also called as Hives. It is a red and sometimes itchy bumps on your skin." .
:SE744 :hasReference :R028 .

:SE745 :hasSideEffectDescription "A fever is a body temperature that is higher than normal. A normal temperature can vary from person to person, but it is usually around 98.6 °F (37 °C). A fever is not a disease. It is usually a sign that your body is trying to fight an illness or infection." .
:SE745 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE745 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE745 :hasReference :R212 .

:SE746 :hasReference :R144 .
:SE746 :hasSideEffectDescription "Serum sickness is a reaction that is similar to an allergy. The immune reacts to medicines that contain proteins used to treat immune conditions. It can also react to antiserum, the liquid part of blood that contains antibodies given to a person to help protect them against germs or poisonous substances." .
:SE746 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE746 :hasReference :R028 .

:SE747 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE747 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE747 :hasSideEffectDescription "Arthralgia is an alternative name of joint pain. It can affect one or more joints. Joint pain can be caused by many types of injuries or conditions. It may be linked to arthritis, bursitis, and muscle pain." .
:SE747 :hasReference :R191 .

:SE748 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylaxis is a seroius allergic reaction. It can began very quickly, and symptoms may be life-threatening." .
:SE748 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE748 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE748 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE749 :hasSideEffectDescription "Thrombocytopenia means there is an abnormally low amount of platelets. Platelets are parts of the blood that help blood to clot. This condition is sometimes associated with abnormal bleeding." .
:SE749 :hasReference :R149 .
:SE749 :hasReference :R028 .
:SE749 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE750 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE750 :hasReference :R224 .
:SE750 :hasSideEffectDescription "Leukopenia is a low white blood count." .
:SE750 :hasReference :R028 .

:SE751 :hasSideEffectDescription "Eosinophils are a type of white blood cell. They help fight off infections and play a role in your body's immune response. They can also build up and cause inflammation." .
:SE751 :hasReference :R151 .
:SE751 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE751 :hasReference :R028 .

:SE752 :hasReference :R163 .
:SE752 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE752 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE752 :hasReference :R029 .

:SE753 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE753 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .
:SE753 :hasReference :R132 .
:SE753 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE754 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE754 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE754 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE754 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE755 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE755 :hasSideEffectDescription "Having dry mouth, also called xerostomia, means that you don't have enough saliva to keep your mouth wet. Everyone has a dry mouth once in a while, like when you are nervous or stressed. But if you have a dry mouth all or most of the time, it can be uncomfortable. It can make chewing, swallowing, and even talking difficult. It also raises your risk for tooth decay or infections in the mouth." .
:SE755 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE755 :hasReference :R233 .

:SE756 :hasReference :R164 .
:SE756 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspepsia is also called as Indigestion. It's a feeling of discomfort or a burning feeling in your upper abdomen. You may have heartburn or belch and feel bloated." .
:SE756 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE756 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE757 :hasReference :R213 .
:SE757 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE757 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE757 :hasSideEffectDescription "Flatulence is also called gas. Gas is air in the intestine that is passed through the rectum. Air that moves from the digestive tract through the mouth is called belching." .

:SE758 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE758 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .
:SE758 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE758 :hasReference :R029 .

:SE759 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE759 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE759 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE759 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vomiting is when you throw up." .

:SE760 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pseudomembranous colitis\nEmail this page to a friend Print Facebook X Pinterest\nPseudomembranous colitis refers to swelling or inflammation of the large intestine (colon) due to an overgrowth of Clostridioides difficile (C difficile) bacteria." .
:SE760 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE760 :hasReference :R203 .
:SE760 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE761 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE761 :hasReference :R143 .
:SE761 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE761 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anaphylactoid Reaction is an anaphylactic-like reaction." .

:SE762 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE762 :hasSideEffectDescription "Angioedema is a swelling that is similar to hives, but the swelling is under the skin instead of on the surface." .
:SE762 :hasReference :R142 .
:SE762 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE763 :hasSideEffectDescription "Arthralgia is an alternative name of joint pain. It can affect one or more joints. Joint pain can be caused by many types of injuries or conditions. It may be linked to arthritis, bursitis, and muscle pain." .
:SE763 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE763 :hasReference :R191 .
:SE763 :hasReference :R029 .

:SE764 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .
:SE764 :hasReference :R154 .
:SE764 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE764 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

