:SE792 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE792 :hasSideEffectDescription "Hemolytic anemia is a condition in which the body does not have enough healthy red blood cells. Red blood cells provide oxygen to body tissues." .
:SE792 :hasReference :R147 .

:SE793 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE793 :hasReference :R179 .
:SE793 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE793 :hasSideEffectDescription "Epistaxis is an alternative name of nose bleed. It is a loss of blood from the tissue lining the nose. Bleeding most often occurs from one nostril only." .

:SE794 :hasSideEffectDescription "Agranulocytosis is when the body has too few granulocytes." .
:SE794 :hasReference :R256 .
:SE794 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE794 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE795 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE795 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE795 :hasSideEffectDescription "Tenesmus is the feeling that you need to pass stools, even though your bowels are already empty. It may involve straining, pain, and cramping." .
:SE795 :hasReference :R283 .

:SE796 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE796 :hasReference :R135 .
:SE796 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE796 :hasSideEffectDescription "Glossitis is a problem in which the tongue is swollen and inflammed. This often makes the surface of the tongue appear smooth." .

:SE797 :hasReference :R184 .
:SE797 :hasSideEffectDescription "Oral Candidiasis, commonly known as thrush, is a yeast infection of the mouth or throat." .
:SE797 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE797 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE798 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE798 :hasReference :R284 .
:SE798 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE798 :hasSideEffectDescription "Heartburn is a painful burning feeling in your chest or throat. It happens when stomach acid backs up into your esophagus, the tube that carries food from your mouth to your stomach." .

:SE799 :hasSideEffectDescription "A nightmare is a bad dream that brings out strong feelings of fear, terror, distress, or anxiety." .
:SE799 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE799 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE799 :hasReference :R197 .

:SE800 :hasReference :R160 .
:SE800 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE800 :hasSideEffectDescription "Vertigo is if you feel like you or the room are spinning." .
:SE800 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE801 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE801 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE801 :hasSideEffectDescription "Chest pain is discomfort or pain that you feel anywhere along the front of your body between your neck and upper abdomen." .
:SE801 :hasReference :R189 .

:SE802 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE802 :hasReference :R285 .
:SE802 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE802 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pleural Effusion is an excess fluid in the pleural space." .

:SE803 :hasSideEffectDescription "Dyspnea is shortness of breath." .
:SE803 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE803 :hasReference :R161 .
:SE803 :hasReference :R029 .

:SE804 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE804 :hasReference :R266 .
:SE804 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE804 :hasSideEffectDescription "Coughing is a reflex that keeps your throat and airways clear. Although it can be annoying, coughing helps your body heal or protect itself." .

:SE805 :hasReference :R223 .
:SE805 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE805 :hasSideEffectDescription "Rhinitis is a condition that includes a runny nose, sneezing, and nasal stuffiness. When environmental allergies (such as hay fever) or a cold are not causing these symptoms, the condition is called nonallergic rhinitis." .
:SE805 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE806 :hasSideEffectDescription "The Coombs test looks for antibodies that may stick to your red blood cells and cause red blood cells to die too early." .
:SE806 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE806 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE806 :hasReference :R278 .

:SE807 :hasReference :R029 .
:SE807 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE807 :hasSideEffectDescription "Pancytopenia can result in extreme tiredness (fatigue) due to low numbers of red blood cells (anemia), frequent infections due to low numbers of white blood cells (neutropenia), and abnormal bleeding due to low numbers of platelets (thrombocytopenia)" .
:SE807 :hasReference :R205 .

:SE808 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE808 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE808 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE808 :hasSideEffectDescription "Nausea is when you feel sick to your stomach, as if you are going to throw up." .

:SE809 :hasReference :R133 .
:SE809 :hasSideEffectDescription "Emesis is also called nausea and vomiting." .
:SE809 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE809 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE810 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE810 :hasSideEffectDescription "Anorexia is an eating disorder that causes people to weigh less than is considered healthy for their age and height, usually by excessive weight loss." .
:SE810 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE810 :hasReference :R132 .

:SE811 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE811 :hasReference :R163 .
:SE811 :hasSideEffectDescription "Abdominal pain is pain that you feel anywhere between your chest and groin. This is often referred to as the stomach region or belly." .
:SE811 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .

:SE812 :hasSideEffectDescription "Diarrhea is loose, watery stools (bowel movements)." .
:SE812 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE812 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE812 :hasReference :R134 .

:SE813 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE813 :hasReference :R210 .
:SE813 :hasSideEffectDescription "Peripheral neuropathy means these nerves don't work properly. Peripheral neuropathy may occur because of damage to a single nerve or a group of nerves. It may also affect nerves in the whole body." .
:SE813 :hasReference :R030 .

:SE814 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE814 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE814 :hasReference :R139 .
:SE814 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythroderma is one alternative name of Exfoliative dermatitis. It is widespread readness of the skin. It also accompanied by scaling, peeling, and flaking of the skin, and may include utching and hair loss." .

:SE815 :hasSideEffectDescription "Erythema Multiforme is an acute skin reaction that comes form an infection or another trigger. EM is a self-limiting condition. This means it usually resolves on its own without treatment." .
:SE815 :hasReference :R030 .
:SE815 :hasPattern :NotSpecified .
:SE815 :hasReference :R154 .

