:SP001 :hasReference :R001 .
:SP001 :hasStewardshipDescription "Should be taken with food: Take w/ meals to avoid GI irritation." .

:SP002 :hasStewardshipDescription "Drink plenty of fluids to reduce risk of esophageal irritation & ulceration." .
:SP002 :hasReference :R001 .

:SP003 :hasStewardshipDescription "Store at temperatures not exceeding 30°C." .
:SP003 :hasReference :R001 .

:SP004 :hasStewardshipDescription "May be taken with or without food." .
:SP004 :hasReference :R002 .

:SP005 :hasStewardshipDescription "Store at temperatures not exceeding 30°C." .
:SP005 :hasReference :R002 .

:SP006 :hasStewardshipDescription "All patients taking doxycycline should be advised: to avoid excessive sunlight or artificial ultraviolet light while receiving doxycycline and to discontinue therapy if phototoxicity (e.g., skin eruption, etc.) occurs. Sunscreen or sunblock should be considered." .
:SP006 :hasReference :R002 .

:SP007 :hasStewardshipDescription "Doxycycline (Dynadoxy) 100 mg capsule, usual adult dose: 2 capsules or 200 mg on first day in single or divided doses of 1 capsule every 12 hours; then 1 capsule a day thereafter. For severe infections: 1 capsule every 12 hours. Or as prescribed by the physician." .
:SP007 :hasReference :R003 .

:SP008 :hasReference :R003 .
:SP008 :hasStewardshipDescription "For acute gonococcal infections: 200 mg at once and 100 mg at bedtime on the first day, followed by 100 mg twice a day for three days." .

:SP009 :hasStewardshipDescription "As an alternative single visit dose, administer 300 mg at once followed in one hour by a second 300 mg dose." .
:SP009 :hasReference :R003 .

:SP010 :hasStewardshipDescription "The dose may be administered with food, including milk or carbonated beverage as required." .
:SP010 :hasReference :R003 .

:SP011 :hasReference :R003 .
:SP011 :hasStewardshipDescription "Primary and secondary syphilis: 300 mg a day in divided doses for at least 10 days. Treatment should be continued even after the time that symptoms and fever have subsided." .

:SP012 :hasReference :R003 .
:SP012 :hasStewardshipDescription "When used in streptococcal infections, therapy should be continued for 10 days. If gastric irritation occurs, it is recommended that Doxycycline be given with food or milk." .

:SP013 :hasReference :R003 .
:SP013 :hasStewardshipDescription "Store at temperatures not exceeding 30°C. Protect from light." .

:SP014 :hasStewardshipDescription "May be taken with or without food." .
:SP014 :hasReference :R003 .

:SP015 :hasReference :R003 .
:SP015 :hasStewardshipDescription "Take w/ a full glass of water & remain upright for at least 30 min. Take w/ food or milk if GI irritation occurs." .

:SP016 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP016 :hasStewardshipDescription "Patients receiving oral or intravenous (IV) levofloxacin should be well hydrated to prevent formation of highly concentrated urine. Crystalluria and cylindruria have been reported with quinolones." .

:SP017 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin should be given or taken at the same time each day." .
:SP017 :hasReference :R004 .

:SP018 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP018 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin tablet can be taken with or without food. Administer dose at least 2 hours before or 2 hours after antacids containing calcium, magnesium or aluminum, after sucralfate or metal cations such as iron, multivitamin preparations with zinc, or didanosine." .

:SP019 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP019 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin solution for infusion should only be administered by IV infusion. It is NOT for intramuscular, intrathecal, intraperitoneal, or subcutaneous administration." .

:SP020 :hasStewardshipDescription "Rapid or bolus IV infusion must be avoided because it may result to hypotension." .
:SP020 :hasReference :R004 .

:SP021 :hasStewardshipDescription "As with other parenteral antibiotic therapy in general, administration of levofloxacin solution for infusion should be continued for a minimum of 48 to 72 hours after the patient has become afebrile or evidence of bacterial eradication has been obtained." .
:SP021 :hasReference :R004 .

:SP022 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP022 :hasStewardshipDescription "It is usually possible to switch from initial IV treatment to the oral route after a few days, depending on the patient's condition and the physician's discretion." .

:SP023 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP023 :hasStewardshipDescription "Observe strict aseptic technique when inserting the cannula of the infusion set into the spout of levofloxacin solution for infusion." .

:SP024 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP024 :hasStewardshipDescription "The cannula of the infusion set should be inserted fully and not halfway into the spout of the levofloxacin solution for infusion container to avoid leakage." .

:SP025 :hasReference :R004 .
:SP025 :hasStewardshipDescription "If the same IV line is used for sequential infusion of several different drugs, the line should be flushed before and after infusion of levofloxacin IV with an infusion solution compatible with levofloxacin IV and with any other drugs administered via this common line." .

:SP026 :hasStewardshipDescription "Store at temperatures not exceeding 30°C. Protect from light and moisture." .
:SP026 :hasReference :R004 .

:SP027 :hasReference :R005 .
:SP027 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin (Levocin) tablets are administered once or twice daily." .

:SP028 :hasReference :R005 .
:SP028 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin (Levocin) should be swallowed without crushing and with sufficient amount of liquid." .

:SP029 :hasReference :R005 .
:SP029 :hasStewardshipDescription "The tablets may be taken during meals or between meals." .

:SP030 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin (Levocin) tablets should be administered at least two hours before or two hours after antacids containing magnesium, aluminum, as well as sucralfate, metal cations such as iron, and multivitamin preparations with zinc." .
:SP030 :hasReference :R005 .

:SP031 :hasReference :R005 .
:SP031 :hasStewardshipDescription "Rapid or bolus intravenous infusion must be avoided." .

:SP032 :hasReference :R005 .
:SP032 :hasStewardshipDescription "Administered by slow infusion over 60 minutes every 24 hours or 750 mg administered by slow infusion over 90 minutes every 24 hours." .

:SP033 :hasReference :R005 .
:SP033 :hasStewardshipDescription "Levofloxacin (Levocin) I.V. Infusion should not be mixed with heparin or alkaline solutions (e.g., sodium hydrogen carbonate)." .

:SP034 :hasStewardshipDescription "Swallow whole, do not crush." .
:SP034 :hasReference :R005 .

